WEBVTT

1
00:01:14.449 --> 00:01:15.867
Are you the guys from Washington?

2
00:01:15.951 --> 00:01:17.786
You get many other visitors out here?

3
00:01:17.869 --> 00:01:19.580
How long you been on-site?

4
00:01:19.705 --> 00:01:20.914
Since this morning.

5
00:01:21.039 --> 00:01:23.709
A Russian oil team
called it in about 18 hours ago.

6
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:26.378
How come nobody spotted it before?

7
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:28.380
It's really not that surprising.

8
00:01:28.463 --> 00:01:30.674
This landscape's changing all the time.

9
00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:32.551
You got any idea
what this thing is exactly?

10
00:01:32.676 --> 00:01:34.761
I don't know.
It's probably a weather balloon.

11
00:01:34.886 --> 00:01:36.096
I don't think so.

12
00:01:36.179 --> 00:01:38.460
You know. we don't have
the equipment for a job like this.

13
00:01:38.682 --> 00:01:40.934
How long before
we can start craning it out?

14
00:01:41.268 --> 00:01:42.936
I don't think you quite understand.

15
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:45.981
You guys are gonna need
one hell of a crane.

16
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:05.792
(Whirring)

17
00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.196
Base. we 're in.

18
00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:35.489
Man on radio: Copy that.

19
00:02:40.661 --> 00:02:41.828
What is this?

20
00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:58.470
Careful.

21
00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:20.701
Lieutenant!

22
00:03:23.787 --> 00:03:24.955
What is it?

23
00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:26.790
My god.

24
00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:29.501
Base. get me a line to the colonel.

25
00:03:30.127 --> 00:03:31.712
Man on radio: It's 3:00 am. sir.

26
00:03:31.795 --> 00:03:36.299
I don't care what time it is.
This one's waited long enough.

27
00:03:41.805 --> 00:03:43.140
(Gunfire)

28
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:45.058
(Panting)

29
00:03:50.605 --> 00:03:51.732
(Speaking Norwegian)

30
00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:52.899
They've come for it!

31
00:03:53.191 --> 00:03:54.776
They have before.

32
00:03:56.403 --> 00:03:57.779
Not like this.

33
00:03:57.988 --> 00:03:59.030
Let them come.

34
00:03:59.114 --> 00:04:00.532
They'll never find it.

35
00:04:00.741 --> 00:04:02.117
(Rumbling)

36
00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:05.996
(Metal rattling)

37
00:04:10.625 --> 00:04:11.918
(Rumbling stops)

38
00:04:15.130 --> 00:04:16.298
(Yelling)

39
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.010
(Machine whirring)

40
00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:36.985
(Car engine stops)

41
00:04:39.821 --> 00:04:40.947
(Car door slams)

42
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:49.039
Open it!

43
00:04:49.164 --> 00:04:50.332
(Grunting)

44
00:04:51.041 --> 00:04:52.793
Quickly. before he gets...

45
00:05:04.805 --> 00:05:08.600
Schmidt: It has taken me a long time
to find this place.

46
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:12.896
You should be commended.

47
00:05:13.021 --> 00:05:14.105
Help him up.

48
00:05:18.401 --> 00:05:21.905
I think that you are
a man of great vision.

49
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:24.366
And. in this way. we are much alike.

50
00:05:24.449 --> 00:05:26.034
I am nothing like you.

51
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:27.577
No. of course. but

52
00:05:28.078 --> 00:05:33.083
what others see as superstition.
you and I know to be a science.

53
00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:35.585
What you seek is just a legend.

54
00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:38.088
Then why make such an effort
to conceal it?

55
00:05:58.525 --> 00:06:03.321
The tesseract was the Jewel
of Odin's treasure room.

56
00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:10.996
It is not something one buries.

57
00:06:11.872 --> 00:06:15.959
But I think it is close. yes?

58
00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:18.044
I cannot help you.

59
00:06:18.128 --> 00:06:22.716
No. But maybe
you can help your village.

60
00:06:23.174 --> 00:06:28.179
You must have some friends out there.
Some little grandchildren. perhaps?

61
00:06:28.763 --> 00:06:31.057
I have no need for them to die.

62
00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:32.893
(Tank gun whirring)

63
00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:36.229
(Tank gun locks)

64
00:06:44.946 --> 00:06:46.990
Yggdrasil.

65
00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:50.076
Schmidt: Tree of the world.

66
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:54.039
Guardian of wisdom.

67
00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:58.209
And fate. also.

68
00:07:29.157 --> 00:07:33.745
And the fcihrer digs for trinkets
in the desert.

69
00:07:37.248 --> 00:07:40.251
You have never seen this. have you?

70
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:44.255
It's not for the eyes of ordinary men.

71
00:07:44.339 --> 00:07:45.966
Exactly.

72
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:52.722
- Give the order to open fire.
- (Speaking German)

73
00:07:52.806 --> 00:07:53.807
Fool!

74
00:07:54.265 --> 00:07:56.685
You cannot control the power you hold.

75
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:57.978
You will burn!

76
00:07:58.979 --> 00:08:00.647
I already have.

77
00:08:13.201 --> 00:08:15.203
Enlistment officer:
O'Connell. Michael.

78
00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.039
Kaminsky. Henry.

79
00:08:18.164 --> 00:08:20.208
Steve: Boy. a lot of guys
getting killed over there.

80
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:22.335
Enlistment officer:
Rogers. Steven.

81
00:08:23.169 --> 00:08:26.214
It kind of makes you think twice
about enlisting. huh?

82
00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:27.799
Nope.

83
00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:32.303
Rogers.

84
00:08:38.393 --> 00:08:41.104
- What did your father die of?
- Mustard gas.

85
00:08:41.896 --> 00:08:45.150
He was in the 107th infantry.
I was hoping I could be assigned...

86
00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:47.902
- Your mother?
- She was a nurse in a tb ward.

87
00:08:48.111 --> 00:08:50.155
Got hit. Couldn't shake it.

88
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:56.661
- Sorry. son.
- Look. just give me a chance.

89
00:08:56.745 --> 00:08:59.289
You'd be ineligible
on your asthma alone.

90
00:08:59.831 --> 00:09:00.991
Is there anything you can do?

91
00:09:01.249 --> 00:09:02.667
I'm doing it.

92
00:09:03.126 --> 00:09:04.294
I'm saving your life.

93
00:09:08.298 --> 00:09:10.925
Announcer:
War continues to ravage Europe.

94
00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:13.928
But help is on the way.

95
00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:19.392
Every able-bodied young man is
lining up to serve his country.

96
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.939
Even little Timmy is doing his part

97
00:09:25.065 --> 00:09:27.067
collecting scrap metal.

98
00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:29.027
Nice work. Timmy!

99
00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:30.236
Man: Who cares?

100
00:09:30.737 --> 00:09:32.238
Play the movie already!

101
00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:34.240
Hey. you wanna show some respect?

102
00:09:34.324 --> 00:09:35.575
Announcer: Meanwhile. overseas.

103
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:38.787
our brave boys are showing
the axis powers that the price

104
00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:40.580
of freedom is never too high.

105
00:09:40.705 --> 00:09:43.124
Man: Let's go! Get on with it!

106
00:09:43.958 --> 00:09:45.668
Hey. just start the cartoon!

107
00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:46.961
Hey. you wanna shut up?

108
00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:50.465
Announcer: Together with
allied forces. we 7! Face any threat.

109
00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:51.883
no matter the size.

110
00:09:52.092 --> 00:09:53.176
(Steve grunting)

111
00:09:56.387 --> 00:09:57.555
(Steve grunting)

112
00:10:05.897 --> 00:10:07.690
(Panting)

113
00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:11.236
You just don't know when to give up.
do you?

114
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:13.696
I can do this all day.

115
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:19.911
Soldier: Hey!

116
00:10:19.994 --> 00:10:21.579
Pick on someone your own size.

117
00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:24.124
(Grunting)

118
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:32.215
Sometimes I think
you like getting punched.

119
00:10:32.799 --> 00:10:34.384
I had him on the ropes.

120
00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:36.636
How many times is this?

121
00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:40.140
Oh. you're from paramus now?

122
00:10:40.431 --> 00:10:43.143
You know it's illegal to lie
on the enlistment form.

123
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:44.602
And seriously. Jersey?

124
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.856
You get your orders?

125
00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:51.442
The 107th.

126
00:10:51.943 --> 00:10:53.444
Sergeant James Barnes.

127
00:10:54.112 --> 00:10:56.364
shipping out for england
first thing tomorrow.

128
00:10:59.242 --> 00:11:00.827
I should be going.

129
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:05.497
Come on. man.

130
00:11:06.249 --> 00:11:09.169
My last night!
I got to get you cleaned up.

131
00:11:09.252 --> 00:11:10.670
Why? Where are we going?

132
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:12.255
The future.

133
00:11:17.051 --> 00:11:19.095
Bucky: I don't see what the problem is.

134
00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:21.764
You're about to be
the last eligible man in New York.

135
00:11:22.056 --> 00:11:24.475
You know there's
three and a half million women here?

136
00:11:25.018 --> 00:11:26.436
Well. I'd settle for just one.

137
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.229
Good thing I took care of that.

138
00:11:28.688 --> 00:11:29.856
Hey. bucky!

139
00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:34.277
What'd you tell her about me?

140
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:36.446
Only the good stuff.

141
00:11:37.405 --> 00:11:40.491
Announcer over pa: Welcome to
the modern marvels pavilion

142
00:11:40.617 --> 00:11:43.453
and the world of tomorrow.

143
00:11:43.786 --> 00:11:47.582
A greater world. A better world.

144
00:11:48.458 --> 00:11:49.834
(Women clamoring)

145
00:11:50.877 --> 00:11:53.379
Oh. my god! It's starting! (Giggles)

146
00:11:53.922 --> 00:11:55.048
(Applause)

147
00:11:55.673 --> 00:11:58.426
Female announcer: Ladies
and gentlemen. Mr. Howard stark!

148
00:11:59.052 --> 00:12:00.929
(Swing music playing)

149
00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:10.480
Woman: I love you. Howard!

150
00:12:12.815 --> 00:12:14.692
Ladies and gentlemen.

151
00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:19.614
what if I told you that in just
a few short years. your automobile

152
00:12:19.906 --> 00:12:22.659
won't even have to
touch the ground at all?

153
00:12:22.825 --> 00:12:24.410
(Audience gasping)

154
00:12:24.494 --> 00:12:26.955
Yes. Thanks. Mandy.

155
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:29.499
With stark gravitic
reversion technology

156
00:12:29.707 --> 00:12:31.542
you'll be able to do just that.

157
00:12:32.043 --> 00:12:34.254
(Mechanical humming)

158
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:41.344
Holy cow.

159
00:12:47.183 --> 00:12:48.351
(Sparking)

160
00:12:53.523 --> 00:12:55.692
I did say a few years. didn't I?

161
00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:57.443
(Applauding)

162
00:13:01.864 --> 00:13:03.533
(Chuckung)

163
00:13:04.367 --> 00:13:07.537
Hey. Steve. what do you say
we treat these girls...

164
00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:15.586
(Giggles)

165
00:13:16.546 --> 00:13:18.339
Come on. soldier.

166
00:13:23.177 --> 00:13:25.489
Bucky: Come on. You're kind of
missing the point of a double date.

167
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:26.889
We're taking the girls dancing.

168
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:29.017
You go ahead. I'll catch up with you.

169
00:13:31.978 --> 00:13:33.980
You're really going to do this again?

170
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:35.541
Well. it's a fair. I'm gonna try my luck.

171
00:13:35.565 --> 00:13:37.525
As who. Steve from Ohio?

172
00:13:37.608 --> 00:13:39.777
They'll catch you.
Or worse. they'll actually take you.

173
00:13:40.611 --> 00:13:41.880
Look. I know
you don't think I can do this.

174
00:13:41.904 --> 00:13:43.465
This isn't a back alley. Steve. It's war.

175
00:13:43.489 --> 00:13:45.551
Steve: I know it's a war.
Bucky: Why are you so keen to fight?

176
00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:47.428
- There are so many importantjobs.
- What do you want me to do?

177
00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:49.412
Collect scrap metal
in my little red wagon?

178
00:13:49.537 --> 00:13:51.140
- Yes. Why not?
- I'm not gonna sit in a factory. bucky.

179
00:13:51.164 --> 00:13:53.624
Bucky. come on.
There are men laying down their lives.

180
00:13:54.584 --> 00:13:56.794
I got no right to do any less than them.

181
00:13:56.919 --> 00:13:59.505
That's what you don't understand.
This isn't about me.

182
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:03.217
Right. 'Cause you got nothing to prove.

183
00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:08.848
Woman: Hey. sarge!
Are we going dancing?

184
00:14:10.183 --> 00:14:11.934
Yes. we are.

185
00:14:17.648 --> 00:14:19.984
Don't do anything stupid until I get back.

186
00:14:20.068 --> 00:14:21.194
How can I?

187
00:14:21.652 --> 00:14:23.571
You're taking all the stupid with you.

188
00:14:26.157 --> 00:14:28.743
- You're a punk.
- Jerk.

189
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.287
Be careful.

190
00:14:34.707 --> 00:14:36.209
Don't win the war till I get there!

191
00:14:41.297 --> 00:14:44.258
Bucky: Come on. girls.
They're playing our song.

192
00:15:00.566 --> 00:15:02.193
(Inaudible whispering)

193
00:15:03.653 --> 00:15:04.987
Wait here.

194
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:08.491
- Is there a problem?
- Just wait here.

195
00:15:27.427 --> 00:15:28.594
Thank you.

196
00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:37.687
You want to go overseas.
Kill some Nazis.

197
00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:40.523
Excuse me?

198
00:15:40.690 --> 00:15:42.442
Dr. Abraham erskine.

199
00:15:42.525 --> 00:15:45.236
I represent
the strategic scientific reserve.

200
00:15:45.570 --> 00:15:46.737
Steve Rogers.

201
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:52.618
Where are you from?

202
00:15:53.119 --> 00:15:57.331
Queens. 73rd street
and utopia parkway.

203
00:15:57.623 --> 00:15:59.625
Before that. Germany.

204
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:02.753
- This troubles you?
- No.

205
00:16:03.713 --> 00:16:05.673
Where are you from. Mr. Rogers?

206
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:07.717
Is it new haven?

207
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.344
Or paramus?

208
00:16:11.345 --> 00:16:13.681
Five exams in five different cities.

209
00:16:13.764 --> 00:16:14.640
That might not be the right file.

210
00:16:14.724 --> 00:16:16.726
No. it's not the exams I'm interested in.

211
00:16:16.809 --> 00:16:18.769
It's the five tries.

212
00:16:19.854 --> 00:16:24.066
But you didn't answer my question.
Do you want to kill Nazis?

213
00:16:26.944 --> 00:16:28.070
Is this a test?

214
00:16:29.489 --> 00:16:30.656
Yes.

215
00:16:33.743 --> 00:16:35.578
I don't want to kill anyone.

216
00:16:36.204 --> 00:16:39.373
I don't like bullies.
I don't care where they're from.

217
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:42.376
Well. there are already

218
00:16:42.502 --> 00:16:44.420
so many big men fighting this war.

219
00:16:44.754 --> 00:16:46.797
Maybe what we need now is a little guy.
huh?

220
00:16:48.758 --> 00:16:50.343
I can offer you a chance.

221
00:16:51.802 --> 00:16:53.638
Only a chance.

222
00:16:53.763 --> 00:16:55.431
- I'll take it.
- Good.

223
00:16:56.724 --> 00:17:00.520
So where is
the little guy from? Actually?

224
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:02.688
Brooklyn.

225
00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:07.443
Congratulations. soldier.

226
00:17:12.323 --> 00:17:13.824
(Breathes deeply)

227
00:17:31.634 --> 00:17:33.844
Schmidt: Are you ready. Dr. Zola?

228
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:38.724
My machine requires
the most delicate calibration.

229
00:17:40.434 --> 00:17:42.436
Forgive me if I seem overcautious.

230
00:17:42.853 --> 00:17:45.064
Are you certain
that those conductors of yours

231
00:17:45.189 --> 00:17:49.277
can withstand the energy surge
long enough for transference?

232
00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:50.861
Zola: With this artifact

233
00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:52.863
I am certain of nothing.

234
00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:55.700
I fear it may not work at all.

235
00:18:26.772 --> 00:18:28.899
(Machine humming)

236
00:18:32.862 --> 00:18:33.863
Twenty percent.

237
00:18:36.115 --> 00:18:37.617
Forty.

238
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:41.662
Sixty.

239
00:18:44.457 --> 00:18:46.292
Stabilizing at 70%.

240
00:18:48.502 --> 00:18:52.089
I have not come all this way
for safety. doctor.

241
00:19:06.812 --> 00:19:08.856
(Low rumbling)

242
00:19:10.733 --> 00:19:12.234
What was that?

243
00:19:12.943 --> 00:19:15.821
I must congratulate you. arnim.

244
00:19:15.905 --> 00:19:19.158
Your designs do not disappoint.

245
00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:23.704
Though they may require
some slight reinforcement.

246
00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:26.707
The exchange is stable.

247
00:19:27.124 --> 00:19:28.751
Amazing!

248
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:31.337
The energy we have just collected

249
00:19:31.462 --> 00:19:34.382
could power my designs.
All my designs.

250
00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:39.345
This will change the war.

251
00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:41.972
Dr. Zola.

252
00:19:43.140 --> 00:19:46.143
this will change the world.

253
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:50.606
Officer: Ready. exercise!

254
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:52.483
Peggy: Recruits. attention!

255
00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:54.902
Gentlemen. I'm agent Carter.

256
00:19:55.319 --> 00:19:57.863
I supervise all operations
for this division.

257
00:19:58.322 --> 00:20:00.157
Hodge: What's with the accent.
queen Victoria?

258
00:20:01.367 --> 00:20:03.369
I thought I was signing up
for the us. Army.

259
00:20:03.577 --> 00:20:04.704
What's your name. soldier?

260
00:20:04.954 --> 00:20:06.789
Gilmore hodge. your majesty.

261
00:20:06.914 --> 00:20:08.582
Step fonnard. hodge.

262
00:20:10.209 --> 00:20:11.752
Put your right foot fonnard.

263
00:20:12.962 --> 00:20:14.422
Mmm... we gonna wrassle?

264
00:20:16.173 --> 00:20:18.676
'Cause I got a few moves
I know you'll like.

265
00:20:21.470 --> 00:20:22.847
Phillips: Agent Carter!

266
00:20:23.013 --> 00:20:24.473
Peggy: Colonel Phillips.

267
00:20:24.598 --> 00:20:27.601
I can see that you are
breaking in the candidates. That's good!

268
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:29.603
Get your ass up out of that dirt

269
00:20:29.687 --> 00:20:32.457
and stand in that line at attention till
somebody comes tells you what to do.

270
00:20:32.481 --> 00:20:34.066
Yes. sir!

271
00:20:37.194 --> 00:20:39.613
General patton has said

272
00:20:40.030 --> 00:20:43.868
that wars are fought with weapons.
but they are won by men.

273
00:20:43.993 --> 00:20:47.413
We are going to win this war
because we have the best men.

274
00:20:51.876 --> 00:20:53.878
And because they are
going to get better.

275
00:20:54.003 --> 00:20:56.005
Much better.

276
00:20:57.006 --> 00:21:00.676
Phillips: The strategic scientific
reserve is an allied effort

277
00:21:00.843 --> 00:21:03.095
made up of
the best minds in the free world.

278
00:21:04.305 --> 00:21:05.139
(Whistle blowing)

279
00:21:05.222 --> 00:21:07.391
Our goal is
to create the best army in history.

280
00:21:08.058 --> 00:21:09.894
But every army starts with one man.

281
00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:11.997
- Officer: Rogers! Get off of there!
- (Men laughing)

282
00:21:12.021 --> 00:21:14.231
At the end of this week.
we will choose that man.

283
00:21:14.857 --> 00:21:18.444
He will be the first
in a new breed of super-soldier.

284
00:21:20.654 --> 00:21:21.739
(Grunting)

285
00:21:24.742 --> 00:21:26.994
Officer: Rogers! Get that rifle out
of the mud!

286
00:21:27.077 --> 00:21:31.916
And they will personally escort
Adolf Hitler to the gates of hell.

287
00:21:32.041 --> 00:21:34.251
Officer: Pick up the pace. ladies!

288
00:21:35.085 --> 00:21:38.464
Let's go. let's go! Double time!

289
00:21:38.839 --> 00:21:41.634
Come on! Faster! Faster!

290
00:21:42.134 --> 00:21:44.303
Move! Move!

291
00:21:44.720 --> 00:21:46.722
Squad. halt!

292
00:21:47.264 --> 00:21:49.642
That flag means
we're only at the halfway point.

293
00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:53.771
First man to bring it to me
gets a ride back with agent Carter.

294
00:21:53.896 --> 00:21:55.523
Move. move!

295
00:21:56.482 --> 00:21:58.275
Come on! Get up there!

296
00:21:58.526 --> 00:22:01.153
If that's all you got.
this army's in trouble!

297
00:22:01.278 --> 00:22:03.030
Get up there. hodge!

298
00:22:03.113 --> 00:22:05.574
Come on! Get up there!

299
00:22:07.117 --> 00:22:09.703
Nobody's got that flag in 17 years!

300
00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:14.667
Now fall back into line! Come on. fall in!

301
00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:17.127
Let's go! Get back into formation!

302
00:22:19.505 --> 00:22:21.799
Rogers! I said fall in!

303
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:34.311
(Car engine starting up)

304
00:22:38.148 --> 00:22:39.567
Steve: Thank you. sir.

305
00:22:48.325 --> 00:22:50.578
Peggy: Faster. ladies! Come on.

306
00:22:50.953 --> 00:22:53.113
My grandmother has more life in her.
god rest her soul.

307
00:22:53.163 --> 00:22:54.331
(Grunting)

308
00:22:54.623 --> 00:22:55.791
Move it!

309
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:58.019
You're not really thinking
about picking Rogers. are you?

310
00:22:58.043 --> 00:23:00.963
I'm more than just thinking about it.
He is the clear choice.

311
00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:04.216
When you brought a 90-pound
asthmatic onto my army base.

312
00:23:04.341 --> 00:23:05.944
I let it slide.
I thought. "what the hell."

313
00:23:05.968 --> 00:23:07.612
Maybe he'd be useful to you.
like a gerbil.

314
00:23:07.636 --> 00:23:08.876
I never thought you'd pick him.

315
00:23:12.433 --> 00:23:14.953
You stick a needle in that kid's arm.
it's gonna go right through him.

316
00:23:14.977 --> 00:23:17.354
- Peggy: Come on. girls.
- Look at that.

317
00:23:18.314 --> 00:23:19.773
He's making me cry.

318
00:23:19.857 --> 00:23:22.359
I am looking for qualities
beyond the physical.

319
00:23:22.443 --> 00:23:24.945
Do you know how long it took
to set up this project?

320
00:23:25.029 --> 00:23:27.799
All the groveling I had to do in front of
senator what's-his-name's committees?

321
00:23:27.823 --> 00:23:29.950
Brandt. Yes. I know.
I am well aware of your efforts.

322
00:23:30.034 --> 00:23:33.120
Then throw me a bone.
Hodge passed every test we gave him.

323
00:23:33.203 --> 00:23:35.122
He's big. he's fast. He obeys orders.

324
00:23:35.205 --> 00:23:36.790
- He's a soldier.
- He is a bully.

325
00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:39.793
You don't win wars
with niceness. doctor.

326
00:23:43.213 --> 00:23:46.008
You win wars with guts.

327
00:23:48.093 --> 00:23:49.136
Grenade!

328
00:23:53.766 --> 00:23:55.184
Steve: Get away!

329
00:23:55.559 --> 00:23:57.019
Get back!

330
00:24:04.151 --> 00:24:05.819
Officer: It was a dummy grenade.

331
00:24:06.904 --> 00:24:08.989
All clear. Back in formation.

332
00:24:13.285 --> 00:24:14.285
(Panting) Is this a test?

333
00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:17.289
He's still skinny.

334
00:24:23.253 --> 00:24:24.254
(Knocking)

335
00:24:25.673 --> 00:24:27.299
- May I?
- Yeah.

336
00:24:27.675 --> 00:24:29.301
(Big band music
playing on radio)

337
00:24:30.678 --> 00:24:32.096
Can't sleep?

338
00:24:32.638 --> 00:24:34.431
- I got the jitters. I guess.
- (Laughs)

339
00:24:35.099 --> 00:24:36.266
Me. too.

340
00:24:38.268 --> 00:24:39.687
Can I ask you a question?

341
00:24:39.812 --> 00:24:41.271
Just one?

342
00:24:43.273 --> 00:24:44.858
Why me?

343
00:24:47.861 --> 00:24:50.656
I suppose that is
the only question that matters.

344
00:24:53.867 --> 00:24:56.870
This is from augsburg. My city.

345
00:24:59.415 --> 00:25:00.499
So many people forget

346
00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:03.252
that the first country the Nazis invaded
was their own.

347
00:25:03.877 --> 00:25:07.131
You know. after the last war.
my people struggled.

348
00:25:07.256 --> 00:25:10.134
They felt weak. They felt small.

349
00:25:10.259 --> 00:25:12.177
And then Hitler comes along
with the marching

350
00:25:12.302 --> 00:25:15.305
and the big show and the flags.
(Stammering)

351
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:20.477
And he hears of me. My work.
And he finds me.

352
00:25:20.561 --> 00:25:21.979
And he says. "you."

353
00:25:22.896 --> 00:25:24.648
He says. "you will make us strong."

354
00:25:25.274 --> 00:25:28.110
Well. I am not interested.

355
00:25:29.361 --> 00:25:31.864
So he sends the head of hydra.

356
00:25:32.364 --> 00:25:34.366
his research division.

357
00:25:34.491 --> 00:25:37.244
A brilliant scientist by the name
of Johann schmidt.

358
00:25:37.327 --> 00:25:39.913
Now. schmidt is
a member of the inner circle.

359
00:25:39.997 --> 00:25:41.165
And he is ambitious.

360
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:47.087
He and Hitler share a passion for
occult power and teutonic myth.

361
00:25:47.713 --> 00:25:50.758
Hitler uses his fantasies
to inspire his followers.

362
00:25:50.883 --> 00:25:52.593
But for schmidt. it is not fantasy.

363
00:25:53.177 --> 00:25:56.221
For him. it is real.
He has become convinced

364
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:58.766
that there is a great power
hidden in the earth.

365
00:25:58.891 --> 00:26:00.184
left here by the gods.

366
00:26:00.309 --> 00:26:03.103
waiting to be seized by a superior man.

367
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:08.567
So when he hears about my formula
and what it can do. he cannot resist.

368
00:26:11.570 --> 00:26:14.364
Schmidt must become
that superior man.

369
00:26:19.953 --> 00:26:21.121
Did it make him stronger?

370
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.414
Yeah.

371
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.834
But there were other effects.

372
00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:31.380
The serum was not ready.

373
00:26:32.591 --> 00:26:35.594
But more important. the man.

374
00:26:36.553 --> 00:26:38.847
The serum amplifies
everything that is inside.

375
00:26:38.972 --> 00:26:42.184
so good becomes great.

376
00:26:42.267 --> 00:26:43.977
Bad becomes worse.

377
00:26:49.274 --> 00:26:50.818
This is why you were chosen.

378
00:26:51.985 --> 00:26:55.405
Because a strong man
who has known power all his life

379
00:26:55.531 --> 00:26:57.449
may lose respect for that power.

380
00:26:57.574 --> 00:27:00.786
but a weak man knows
the value of strength.

381
00:27:01.411 --> 00:27:03.247
And knows

382
00:27:03.622 --> 00:27:05.040
compassion.

383
00:27:08.252 --> 00:27:11.004
Thanks. I think.

384
00:27:13.382 --> 00:27:14.508
(Mutters)

385
00:27:16.844 --> 00:27:19.805
Whatever happens tomorrow.
you must promise me one thing.

386
00:27:23.016 --> 00:27:25.185
That you will stay who you are.

387
00:27:27.563 --> 00:27:29.565
Not a perfect soldier.

388
00:27:29.982 --> 00:27:31.066
but

389
00:27:31.358 --> 00:27:33.360
a good man.

390
00:27:38.574 --> 00:27:40.200
To the little guys.

391
00:27:40.284 --> 00:27:41.493
(Chuckles)

392
00:27:42.661 --> 00:27:44.246
No. no. Wait. wait. What I am doing?

393
00:27:44.329 --> 00:27:46.290
No. you have procedure tomorrow.
No fluids.

394
00:27:47.624 --> 00:27:49.418
All right. We'll drink it after.

395
00:27:49.793 --> 00:27:53.255
No. I don't have procedure tomorrow.
Drink it after? I drink it now.

396
00:27:56.717 --> 00:27:59.428
(Opera music playing)

397
00:28:08.645 --> 00:28:11.481
Schmidt: Is there something
in particular you need?

398
00:28:17.529 --> 00:28:20.324
I understand you found him.

399
00:28:21.074 --> 00:28:22.659
See for yourself.

400
00:28:34.838 --> 00:28:36.506
Schmidt: You disapprove.

401
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:40.135
I just don't see
why you need concern yourself.

402
00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:41.929
I can't imagine he will succeed.

403
00:28:44.932 --> 00:28:46.266
Again.

404
00:28:46.475 --> 00:28:50.479
His serum is the allies' only defense
against this power we now possess.

405
00:28:50.562 --> 00:28:54.358
If we take it away from them.
then our victory is assured.

406
00:28:57.569 --> 00:28:59.154
Shall I give the order?

407
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:02.157
It has been given.

408
00:29:04.368 --> 00:29:05.535
Good.

409
00:29:08.288 --> 00:29:09.373
Dr. Zola!

410
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:14.878
What do you think?

411
00:29:21.677 --> 00:29:23.553
A masterpiece.

412
00:29:32.229 --> 00:29:33.855
Boy: We gotta get the ball!

413
00:29:33.939 --> 00:29:35.565
Steve: I know this neighborhood.

414
00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:38.485
I got beat up in that alley.

415
00:29:40.195 --> 00:29:41.321
And that parking lot.

416
00:29:43.615 --> 00:29:45.575
And behind that diner.

417
00:29:45.909 --> 00:29:48.412
Did you have something against
running away?

418
00:29:51.039 --> 00:29:53.500
You start running.
they'll never let you stop.

419
00:29:53.583 --> 00:29:55.585
You stand up. you push back.

420
00:29:55.711 --> 00:29:57.129
They can't say no forever. right?

421
00:29:57.796 --> 00:30:01.425
I know a little of what that's like.
to have every door shut in your face.

422
00:30:02.592 --> 00:30:04.570
I guess I just don't know
why you'd want to join the army

423
00:30:04.594 --> 00:30:06.138
if you were a beautiful dame.

424
00:30:06.346 --> 00:30:07.639
Or a... a woman.

425
00:30:07.848 --> 00:30:09.266
An agent. Not a dame.

426
00:30:09.516 --> 00:30:11.184
You are beautiful. but...

427
00:30:11.935 --> 00:30:14.187
You have no idea
how to talk to a woman. do you?

428
00:30:14.604 --> 00:30:16.924
I think this is the longest conversation
I've had with one.

429
00:30:18.191 --> 00:30:21.611
Women aren't exactly lining up
to dance with a guy they might step on.

430
00:30:22.070 --> 00:30:23.488
You must have danced.

431
00:30:23.613 --> 00:30:26.199
Well. asking a woman to dance
always seemed so terrifying.

432
00:30:27.242 --> 00:30:29.286
And the past few years. it just

433
00:30:29.411 --> 00:30:32.247
didn't seem to matter that much.
I figured I'd wait.

434
00:30:32.664 --> 00:30:33.749
For what?

435
00:30:35.459 --> 00:30:36.793
The right partner.

436
00:30:51.433 --> 00:30:52.684
This way.

437
00:30:56.021 --> 00:30:58.482
- What are we doing here?
- Follow me.

438
00:31:01.443 --> 00:31:02.694
(Bell ringing)

439
00:31:11.661 --> 00:31:14.539
Wonderful weather this morning.
isn't it?

440
00:31:14.664 --> 00:31:16.708
Yes. but I always carry an umbrella.

441
00:31:21.922 --> 00:31:23.340
(Buzzing sound)

442
00:31:30.806 --> 00:31:31.890
(Door unlocking)

443
00:31:53.495 --> 00:31:54.913
(Scientists talking)

444
00:32:14.516 --> 00:32:15.892
Good morning.

445
00:32:17.144 --> 00:32:18.728
Please. not now.

446
00:32:23.733 --> 00:32:24.733
Are you ready?

447
00:32:26.736 --> 00:32:30.532
Good. Take off your shirt. your tie.
and your hat.

448
00:32:36.121 --> 00:32:37.681
Senator Brandt. glad you could make it.

449
00:32:37.747 --> 00:32:39.541
Why exactly am I in Brooklyn?

450
00:32:39.624 --> 00:32:41.460
We needed access to
the city's power grid.

451
00:32:41.585 --> 00:32:43.855
Of course. if you'd have given me
the generators I requisitioned...

452
00:32:43.879 --> 00:32:45.839
A lot of people are
asking for funds. colonel.

453
00:32:45.964 --> 00:32:47.466
Oh. this is...

454
00:32:47.591 --> 00:32:49.217
Fred clemson. state department.

455
00:32:49.342 --> 00:32:50.736
If this project of yours comes through.

456
00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:53.597
we'd like to see it used
for something other than headlines.

457
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:57.392
Jesus. Somebody get that kid
a sandwich.

458
00:33:10.363 --> 00:33:11.490
Comfortable?

459
00:33:13.575 --> 00:33:14.743
It's a little big.

460
00:33:14.826 --> 00:33:15.869
(Chuckung)

461
00:33:16.953 --> 00:33:18.663
You save me any of that schnapps?

462
00:33:19.623 --> 00:33:22.501
Not as much as I should have. Sorry.

463
00:33:22.751 --> 00:33:24.169
Next time.

464
00:33:25.170 --> 00:33:27.380
Mr. Stark. how are your levels?

465
00:33:27.464 --> 00:33:29.799
- Levels at 100%.
- Good.

466
00:33:29.883 --> 00:33:31.635
We may dim half the lights in Brooklyn.

467
00:33:32.177 --> 00:33:34.971
but we are ready as we'll ever be.

468
00:33:35.889 --> 00:33:37.015
Erskine: Agent Carter?

469
00:33:37.098 --> 00:33:39.476
Don't you think you would be
more comfortable in the booth?

470
00:33:39.601 --> 00:33:41.102
- Yes. of course. Sorry.
- Good.

471
00:33:51.446 --> 00:33:52.656
(Thudding over pa)

472
00:33:52.739 --> 00:33:53.782
(Microphone feedback)

473
00:33:53.865 --> 00:33:55.408
Erskine: Do you hear me? Is this on?

474
00:33:56.326 --> 00:33:57.494
Ladies and gentlemen.

475
00:33:58.119 --> 00:34:01.706
today we take not another step
towards annihilation.

476
00:34:01.998 --> 00:34:03.250
but the first step

477
00:34:03.667 --> 00:34:05.752
on the path to peace.

478
00:34:07.879 --> 00:34:11.007
We begin with a series
of microinjections into

479
00:34:11.091 --> 00:34:14.844
the subject's major muscle groups.
The serum infusion

480
00:34:15.262 --> 00:34:18.056
will cause immediate cellular change.

481
00:34:18.723 --> 00:34:21.643
And then. to stimulate growth.

482
00:34:21.726 --> 00:34:25.230
the subject will be
saturated with vita-rays.

483
00:34:32.862 --> 00:34:34.030
That wasn't so bad.

484
00:34:34.864 --> 00:34:36.032
That was penicillin.

485
00:34:39.744 --> 00:34:41.830
Serum infusion beginning in

486
00:34:42.247 --> 00:34:43.331
five.

487
00:34:44.332 --> 00:34:45.458
four.

488
00:34:46.876 --> 00:34:47.876
three.

489
00:34:49.170 --> 00:34:50.880
two.

490
00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:53.174
one.

491
00:35:00.140 --> 00:35:01.558
(Grunting)

492
00:35:03.810 --> 00:35:05.061
Now. Mr. Stark.

493
00:35:28.501 --> 00:35:31.504
Steven? Can you hear me?

494
00:35:31.755 --> 00:35:34.966
Steve: It's probably too late
to go to the bathroom. right?

495
00:35:36.509 --> 00:35:38.136
We will proceed.

496
00:35:42.932 --> 00:35:43.932
(Low rumbling)

497
00:35:50.774 --> 00:35:51.858
Howard: That's 10%.

498
00:35:52.984 --> 00:35:53.984
Twenty percent.

499
00:35:54.235 --> 00:35:55.445
Thirty.

500
00:35:57.947 --> 00:35:59.115
That's 40%.

501
00:36:00.659 --> 00:36:01.785
Vital signs are normal.

502
00:36:01.951 --> 00:36:02.951
That's 50%.

503
00:36:03.662 --> 00:36:04.788
Sixty.

504
00:36:06.331 --> 00:36:07.582
Seventy.

505
00:36:07.666 --> 00:36:09.584
(Steve screaming)

506
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:13.254
Erskine: Steven!

507
00:36:13.963 --> 00:36:15.173
- Steven!
- Shut it down!

508
00:36:15.256 --> 00:36:17.008
Steven!

509
00:36:17.092 --> 00:36:18.134
Shut it down!

510
00:36:18.968 --> 00:36:20.071
Kill the reactor. Mr. Stark!

511
00:36:20.095 --> 00:36:21.846
Turn it off! Kill it! Kill the reactor!

512
00:36:21.971 --> 00:36:23.139
Steve: No!

513
00:36:23.640 --> 00:36:26.142
Don't! I can do this!

514
00:36:33.024 --> 00:36:34.150
Howard: Eighty.

515
00:36:34.901 --> 00:36:36.027
Ninety.

516
00:36:37.237 --> 00:36:39.197
That's 100%.

517
00:36:39.489 --> 00:36:41.825
(Electricity humming)

518
00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:50.625
(Machine powering down)

519
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.846
Mr. Stark?

520
00:37:13.648 --> 00:37:15.608
Steven. Steven.

521
00:37:15.692 --> 00:37:17.026
(Excited chattering)

522
00:37:18.236 --> 00:37:19.654
The son of a bitch did it.

523
00:37:25.994 --> 00:37:27.412
- I did it.
- Yeah. yeah.

524
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:29.205
I think we did it.

525
00:37:29.330 --> 00:37:30.623
You actually did it.

526
00:37:34.502 --> 00:37:36.045
How do you feel?

527
00:37:38.882 --> 00:37:40.633
Taller.

528
00:37:43.553 --> 00:37:44.971
You look taller.

529
00:37:45.054 --> 00:37:46.890
How do you like Brooklyn now. senator?

530
00:37:47.140 --> 00:37:51.019
I can think of some folks in Berlin
who are about to get very nervous.

531
00:37:53.646 --> 00:37:55.857
Brandt: Congratulations. doctor.

532
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.567
Thank you. sir.

533
00:38:05.533 --> 00:38:07.118
(Exclaiming)

534
00:38:08.870 --> 00:38:10.246
Erskine: Stop him!

535
00:38:10.914 --> 00:38:12.332
(Woman screaming)

536
00:38:48.034 --> 00:38:49.619
(Shouting)

537
00:38:52.121 --> 00:38:53.206
(Woman screaming)

538
00:39:14.018 --> 00:39:16.980
Taxi driver: What are you doing?
Buddy. are you all right?

539
00:39:17.063 --> 00:39:18.648
Hey. this guy's been shot!

540
00:39:29.951 --> 00:39:31.035
I had him!

541
00:39:31.536 --> 00:39:33.121
Sorry!

542
00:39:35.456 --> 00:39:36.624
(Panting)

543
00:39:48.469 --> 00:39:49.596
(Exclaiming)

544
00:39:53.099 --> 00:39:54.642
- I'm sorry!
- Man: I don't believe it!

545
00:40:02.483 --> 00:40:04.652
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

546
00:40:57.538 --> 00:40:58.665
(Grunting)

547
00:41:00.583 --> 00:41:01.751
(Crowd screaming)

548
00:41:06.923 --> 00:41:09.509
No! No! Not my son!

549
00:41:10.385 --> 00:41:12.011
- Stop it!
- Don't hurt him!

550
00:41:13.972 --> 00:41:15.098
Get back!

551
00:41:16.265 --> 00:41:17.725
Boy: Let me go!

552
00:41:20.770 --> 00:41:22.313
Woman: Let go of my son!

553
00:41:24.107 --> 00:41:26.234
Woman: No! Don't hurt him!

554
00:41:30.488 --> 00:41:32.323
Wait. don't! Don't!

555
00:41:32.699 --> 00:41:33.699
(Gun clicks)

556
00:41:33.992 --> 00:41:35.118
No! Don't!

557
00:41:41.124 --> 00:41:43.126
Go get him! I can swim!

558
00:41:44.127 --> 00:41:45.211
(Lighter flicking)

559
00:42:20.204 --> 00:42:21.330
(Gasping)

560
00:42:27.086 --> 00:42:28.421
(Grunting)

561
00:42:35.219 --> 00:42:37.555
- Who the hell are you?
- The first of many.

562
00:42:37.972 --> 00:42:39.557
Cutoff one head.

563
00:42:39.640 --> 00:42:41.392
- (grunting in pain)
- (Glass cracking)

564
00:42:41.601 --> 00:42:43.478
Two more shall take its place.

565
00:42:45.980 --> 00:42:47.857
Hail hydra.

566
00:43:07.085 --> 00:43:09.765
Man 1: The fcihrer is not accustomed
to being ignored. herr schmidt.

567
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:12.673
He funds your research because
you promised him weapons.

568
00:43:12.799 --> 00:43:14.675
Man 2: You serve at his pleasure.

569
00:43:14.801 --> 00:43:17.637
He gave you this facility
as a reward for your injuries.

570
00:43:17.720 --> 00:43:20.431
Schmidt: Reward?
Call it what it is. Exile.

571
00:43:20.515 --> 00:43:23.101
I no longer reflect his image
of Aryan perfection.

572
00:43:23.226 --> 00:43:25.478
Man 3: You think this is
about appearances?

573
00:43:25.603 --> 00:43:30.108
Your hydra division has failed to deliver
so much as a rifle in over a year.

574
00:43:30.233 --> 00:43:32.485
And we had learned
through local intelligence

575
00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:35.696
you had mounted a full-scale incursion
into nonnay.

576
00:43:35.822 --> 00:43:37.698
The fcihrer feels... how does he put it?

577
00:43:37.824 --> 00:43:41.119
"The red skull has been indulged
long enough!"

578
00:43:53.131 --> 00:43:54.507
Gentlemen.

579
00:43:57.260 --> 00:44:00.638
you have come to see
the results of our work.

580
00:44:01.931 --> 00:44:03.349
Let me show you.

581
00:44:04.934 --> 00:44:07.520
Hitler speaks of a 1.000-year reich.

582
00:44:07.645 --> 00:44:09.522
but he cannot feed his armies
for a month.

583
00:44:09.647 --> 00:44:13.067
His troops spill their blood
across every field in Europe.

584
00:44:13.151 --> 00:44:17.280
but still he is no closer to
achieving his goals.

585
00:44:17.530 --> 00:44:20.783
And I suppose you still aim
to win this war through magic?

586
00:44:21.450 --> 00:44:25.496
Science. But I understand
your confusion.

587
00:44:25.746 --> 00:44:28.541
Great power has always
baffled primitive men.

588
00:44:28.875 --> 00:44:33.004
Hydra is assembling an arsenal
to destroy my enemies in one stroke.

589
00:44:33.296 --> 00:44:36.382
wherever they are. regardless of
how many forces they possess.

590
00:44:36.507 --> 00:44:37.675
all in a matter of hours.

591
00:44:38.092 --> 00:44:39.427
Your enemies?

592
00:44:39.510 --> 00:44:42.138
My weapons contain
enough destructive power

593
00:44:42.221 --> 00:44:44.807
to decimate
every hostile capital on earth.

594
00:44:47.393 --> 00:44:48.978
Quite simply. gentlemen.

595
00:44:49.896 --> 00:44:52.523
I have harnessed the power of the gods.

596
00:44:52.607 --> 00:44:53.733
(Clears throat)

597
00:44:54.400 --> 00:44:55.318
Thank you. schmidt.

598
00:44:55.401 --> 00:44:56.527
For what?

599
00:44:57.028 --> 00:45:00.364
For making it clear
how obviously mad you are.

600
00:45:00.448 --> 00:45:01.741
Berlin is on this map!

601
00:45:02.617 --> 00:45:04.327
So it is.

602
00:45:06.412 --> 00:45:08.956
You will be punished for your insolence!

603
00:45:09.040 --> 00:45:11.500
You will be brought
before the fcihrer himself!

604
00:45:20.718 --> 00:45:22.720
(Screaming) Schmidt...

605
00:45:27.642 --> 00:45:29.602
My apologies. doctor.

606
00:45:29.727 --> 00:45:34.732
but we both knew hydra could grow
no further in Hitler's shadow.

607
00:45:36.150 --> 00:45:37.276
Hail hydra.

608
00:45:37.944 --> 00:45:39.570
Hail hydra!

609
00:45:44.283 --> 00:45:45.993
Hail hydra!

610
00:45:57.546 --> 00:45:59.298
Think you got enough?

611
00:46:00.675 --> 00:46:04.887
Peggy: Any hope of reproducing the
program is locked in your genetic code.

612
00:46:05.388 --> 00:46:08.224
But without Dr. Erskine.
it would take years.

613
00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:11.269
He deserved more than this.

614
00:46:12.478 --> 00:46:16.107
If it could work only once.
he'd be proud it was you.

615
00:46:18.985 --> 00:46:21.862
Brandt: Colonel Phillips.
my committee is demanding answers.

616
00:46:22.321 --> 00:46:23.781
Great. Why don't we start with how

617
00:46:23.864 --> 00:46:27.076
a German spy got a ride to
my secret installation in your car?

618
00:46:27.201 --> 00:46:28.619
What have we got here?

619
00:46:28.703 --> 00:46:31.789
Speaking modestly. I'm the best
mechanical engineer in this country.

620
00:46:32.206 --> 00:46:34.792
But I don't know what's inside this thing
or how it works.

621
00:46:35.334 --> 00:46:36.770
We're not even close to this technology.

622
00:46:36.794 --> 00:46:38.629
- Then who is?
- Phillips: Hydra.

623
00:46:39.130 --> 00:46:40.810
I'm sure you've been
reading our briefings.

624
00:46:41.007 --> 00:46:43.050
I'm on a number of
committees. colonel.

625
00:46:43.134 --> 00:46:45.428
Hydra is the Nazi deep-science division.

626
00:46:45.511 --> 00:46:49.056
It's led by Johann schmidt.
But he has much bigger ambitions.

627
00:46:49.140 --> 00:46:50.492
Phillips: Hydra is practically a cult.

628
00:46:50.516 --> 00:46:52.436
They worship schmidt.
They think he's invincible.

629
00:46:52.643 --> 00:46:54.163
So. what are you going to do about it?

630
00:46:54.687 --> 00:46:56.207
I spoke to the president this morning.

631
00:46:56.647 --> 00:46:59.442
- As of today. the ssr is being retasked.
- Colonel?

632
00:46:59.525 --> 00:47:02.903
We are taking the fight to hydra.
Pack your bags. agent Carter.

633
00:47:03.029 --> 00:47:04.447
You. too. stark.

634
00:47:04.655 --> 00:47:06.490
We're flying to London tonight.

635
00:47:06.574 --> 00:47:08.743
Sir? If you're going after schmidt.
I want in.

636
00:47:09.076 --> 00:47:11.078
You're an experiment.
You're going to alamogordo.

637
00:47:11.537 --> 00:47:12.663
The serum worked.

638
00:47:12.747 --> 00:47:14.540
I asked for an army
and all I got was you.

639
00:47:15.249 --> 00:47:17.835
You are not enough.

640
00:47:21.964 --> 00:47:23.404
With all due respect to the colonel.

641
00:47:23.924 --> 00:47:25.718
I think we may be missing the point.

642
00:47:26.135 --> 00:47:30.556
I've seen you in action. Steve.
More importantly. the country's seen it.

643
00:47:30.723 --> 00:47:31.849
Papeh

644
00:47:32.641 --> 00:47:34.560
the enlistment lines
have been around the block

645
00:47:34.685 --> 00:47:36.812
since your picture hit the newsstands.

646
00:47:37.229 --> 00:47:40.441
You don't take a soldier.
a symbol like that.

647
00:47:40.566 --> 00:47:42.443
and hide him in a lab.

648
00:47:42.902 --> 00:47:46.781
Son. do you want to serve your country

649
00:47:46.906 --> 00:47:49.909
on the most important battlefield
of the war?

650
00:47:51.243 --> 00:47:53.245
Sir. that's all I want.

651
00:47:53.746 --> 00:47:57.249
Then. congratulations.
You just got promoted.

652
00:47:58.751 --> 00:48:00.211
(Sighing)

653
00:48:00.419 --> 00:48:01.670
I don't know if I can do this.

654
00:48:01.754 --> 00:48:05.132
Nothing to it. You sell a few bonds.
Bonds buy bullets. Bullets kill Nazis.

655
00:48:05.216 --> 00:48:06.258
Bing bang boom.

656
00:48:06.592 --> 00:48:08.260
You're an American hero.

657
00:48:08.552 --> 00:48:10.554
It's just not how
I pictured getting there.

658
00:48:11.263 --> 00:48:13.432
The senator has got
a lot of pull up on the hill.

659
00:48:13.516 --> 00:48:14.683
You play ball with us.

660
00:48:14.767 --> 00:48:16.567
you'll be leading your own platoon
in no time.

661
00:48:16.602 --> 00:48:18.270
Take the shield.

662
00:48:20.606 --> 00:48:21.732
(Big band playing)

663
00:48:21.816 --> 00:48:23.293
(Women singing)
J'who's strong and brave j"

664
00:48:23.317 --> 00:48:27.613
j " here to save the American way? J"

665
00:48:27.696 --> 00:48:30.533
not all of us can storm a beach
or drive a tank.

666
00:48:30.616 --> 00:48:32.493
But there's still a way
all of us can fight.

667
00:48:32.618 --> 00:48:37.248
J" who vows to fight like a man
for what's right. night and day? J"

668
00:48:37.706 --> 00:48:39.208
series e defense bonds.

669
00:48:39.291 --> 00:48:43.003
Each one you buy is a bullet in
the barrel of your best guy's gun.

670
00:48:43.087 --> 00:48:46.715
J" who will campaign door-to-door
for america? J"

671
00:48:46.799 --> 00:48:49.969
j" carry the flag shore to shore
for america? J"

672
00:48:50.052 --> 00:48:53.180
j " from hoboken to spokane j"

673
00:48:53.264 --> 00:48:59.311
j " the star-spangled man with a plan j"

674
00:49:01.730 --> 00:49:04.442
director: Cut. Guys.
don't look at the camera.

675
00:49:04.525 --> 00:49:08.612
J" we can't ignore there's a threat
and a war we must win j"

676
00:49:08.696 --> 00:49:11.449
each one you buy is a bullet in
the barrel of your best guy's gun.

677
00:49:11.532 --> 00:49:16.912
J" who'll hang a noose on the
goose-stepping goons from Berlin? J"

678
00:49:18.497 --> 00:49:21.667
j" who will redeem
heed the call for america? J"

679
00:49:21.917 --> 00:49:25.045
j" who'll rise or fall
give his all for america? J"

680
00:49:25.713 --> 00:49:28.507
j " who's here to prove that we can? J"

681
00:49:28.632 --> 00:49:34.763
j " the star-spangled man with a plan j"

682
00:49:35.055 --> 00:49:37.475
Steve: We all know this is about
trying to win the war.

683
00:49:37.558 --> 00:49:40.686
We can't do that without bullets
and bandages. tanks and tents.

684
00:49:40.769 --> 00:49:42.897
That's where you come in.
Every bond you buy

685
00:49:43.022 --> 00:49:44.422
will help protect someone you love.

686
00:49:44.732 --> 00:49:47.335
- Turn around! He's right behind you!
- Keep our boys armed and ready.

687
00:49:47.359 --> 00:49:50.112
and the Germans will think twice about
trying to get the drop on us.

688
00:49:50.529 --> 00:49:51.572
(Cymbals crashing)

689
00:49:53.949 --> 00:49:57.036
J " stalwart and steady and true j"

690
00:49:57.119 --> 00:50:00.122
(cymbals crashing repeatedly)

691
00:50:01.165 --> 00:50:04.168
J " forceful and ready to defend j"

692
00:50:04.293 --> 00:50:08.047
j " the red. white. and blue j"

693
00:50:08.130 --> 00:50:12.051
j" who'll give the axis the sack
and is smart as a fox? J"

694
00:50:12.134 --> 00:50:15.513
j " far as an eagle will soar j"

695
00:50:15.596 --> 00:50:19.141
j" who's making Adolf
afraid to step out of his box? J"

696
00:50:19.266 --> 00:50:22.186
j " he knows what we 're fighting for j"

697
00:50:22.394 --> 00:50:25.648
j" who waked the giant
that napped in america? J"

698
00:50:25.731 --> 00:50:29.318
j" we know it's no one
but captain america j"

699
00:50:31.070 --> 00:50:32.738
j " who'll finish what they began? J"

700
00:50:32.863 --> 00:50:35.866
j " who'll kick the krauts to Japan? J"

701
00:50:35.950 --> 00:50:39.745
j " the star-spangled man j"

702
00:50:39.870 --> 00:50:42.831
j“ with a j“

703
00:50:43.541 --> 00:50:46.335
j " plan! J"

704
00:50:48.963 --> 00:50:50.089
(music ends)

705
00:50:54.218 --> 00:50:58.138
How many of you are ready to
help me sock old Adolf on the jaw?

706
00:51:02.726 --> 00:51:03.936
Okay.

707
00:51:06.730 --> 00:51:08.941
I need a volunteer.

708
00:51:09.024 --> 00:51:11.211
Man 1: I already volunteered!
How do you think I got here?

709
00:51:11.235 --> 00:51:12.653
(Crowd laughing)

710
00:51:12.861 --> 00:51:14.697
Man 2: Bring back the girls!

711
00:51:18.701 --> 00:51:21.120
I think they only know
the one song. but. um.

712
00:51:21.745 --> 00:51:23.372
I'll see what I can do.

713
00:51:23.747 --> 00:51:25.374
Man 3: You do that. sweetheart.

714
00:51:25.708 --> 00:51:28.544
Nice boots. tinker bell!

715
00:51:29.587 --> 00:51:31.839
Come on. guys.
we 're all on the same team here.

716
00:51:32.047 --> 00:51:34.258
Hey. captain! Sign this!

717
00:51:34.967 --> 00:51:36.594
(Crowd cheering)

718
00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:46.937
Bring back the girls!

719
00:51:48.731 --> 00:51:51.025
(Jaunty piano playing)

720
00:51:51.692 --> 00:51:54.278
Don't worry. pal. They'll warm up to you.
Don't worry.

721
00:52:02.703 --> 00:52:03.954
Peggy: Hello. Steve.

722
00:52:07.625 --> 00:52:09.877
- Hi.
- What are you doing here?

723
00:52:10.002 --> 00:52:12.046
Officially. I'm not here at all.

724
00:52:12.588 --> 00:52:14.506
That was quite a performance.

725
00:52:14.923 --> 00:52:15.923
Yeah.

726
00:52:16.967 --> 00:52:18.802
I had to improvise a little bit.

727
00:52:18.969 --> 00:52:21.597
The crowds I'm used to
are usually more. uh.

728
00:52:22.973 --> 00:52:24.016
twelve.

729
00:52:24.099 --> 00:52:26.226
I understand you're
"america's new hope."

730
00:52:26.310 --> 00:52:28.896
Bond sales take a 10% bump
in every state I visit.

731
00:52:28.979 --> 00:52:30.481
Is that senator Brandt I hear?

732
00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:34.068
At least he's got me doing this.

733
00:52:34.193 --> 00:52:35.903
Phillips would have had me
stuck in a lab.

734
00:52:35.986 --> 00:52:38.614
And these are your only two options?

735
00:52:38.781 --> 00:52:41.200
A lab rat or a dancing monkey?

736
00:52:41.784 --> 00:52:44.620
You were meant for more than this.
you know.

737
00:52:50.417 --> 00:52:51.502
What?

738
00:52:52.920 --> 00:52:55.756
You know. for the longest time.
I dreamed about

739
00:52:56.215 --> 00:52:59.635
coming overseas
and being on the front lines.

740
00:52:59.802 --> 00:53:01.428
serving my country.

741
00:53:02.221 --> 00:53:04.223
I finally got everything I wanted

742
00:53:07.851 --> 00:53:08.894
and I'm wearing tights.

743
00:53:08.977 --> 00:53:10.688
(Car horn honking)

744
00:53:11.522 --> 00:53:12.940
Soldier: Move it. move it!

745
00:53:17.444 --> 00:53:19.084
They look like they've been through hell.

746
00:53:19.863 --> 00:53:20.864
These men more than most.

747
00:53:24.868 --> 00:53:29.873
Schmidt sent out a force to azzano.
Two hundred men went up against him.

748
00:53:30.666 --> 00:53:32.876
and less than 50 returned.

749
00:53:33.711 --> 00:53:36.046
Your audience contained
what was left of the 107th.

750
00:53:36.839 --> 00:53:38.966
The rest were killed or captured.

751
00:53:39.049 --> 00:53:40.676
The 107th?

752
00:53:40.759 --> 00:53:41.802
What?

753
00:53:42.094 --> 00:53:43.554
Come on.

754
00:53:44.555 --> 00:53:45.597
Colonel Phillips.

755
00:53:45.723 --> 00:53:47.659
Well. if it isn't
the star-spangled man with a plan.

756
00:53:47.683 --> 00:53:48.851
What is your plan today?

757
00:53:48.934 --> 00:53:50.370
I need the casualty list from azzano.

758
00:53:50.394 --> 00:53:51.746
You don't get to give me orders. son.

759
00:53:51.770 --> 00:53:54.982
I just need one name.
sergeant James Barnes from the 107th.

760
00:53:55.482 --> 00:53:57.919
You and I are gonna have a
conversation later that you won't enjoy.

761
00:53:57.943 --> 00:53:59.778
Please tell me if he's alive. sir.
B-a-r...

762
00:53:59.862 --> 00:54:01.321
I can spell.

763
00:54:07.119 --> 00:54:11.749
I have signed more of these condolence
letters today than I would care to count.

764
00:54:11.874 --> 00:54:14.001
But the name does sound familiar.

765
00:54:14.710 --> 00:54:15.794
I'm sorry.

766
00:54:20.007 --> 00:54:22.342
What about the others?
Are you planning a rescue mission?

767
00:54:22.718 --> 00:54:24.118
Yes. it's called "winning the war."

768
00:54:25.512 --> 00:54:26.990
But if you know where they are.
why not at least...

769
00:54:27.014 --> 00:54:28.974
They're 30 miles behind the lines

770
00:54:29.057 --> 00:54:31.810
through some of the most
heavily fortified territory in Europe.

771
00:54:31.935 --> 00:54:33.312
We'd lose more men than we'd save.

772
00:54:33.395 --> 00:54:36.195
But I don't expect you to understand that
because you're a chorus girl.

773
00:54:38.317 --> 00:54:39.860
I think I understand just fine.

774
00:54:40.235 --> 00:54:42.070
Well. then understand it
somewhere else.

775
00:54:42.196 --> 00:54:46.533
If I read the posters correctly.
you got some place to be in 30 minutes.

776
00:54:51.330 --> 00:54:53.916
Yes. sir. I do.

777
00:54:57.961 --> 00:54:59.254
If you have something to say.

778
00:54:59.338 --> 00:55:01.924
right now is the perfect time
to keep it to yourself.

779
00:55:06.261 --> 00:55:08.138
What do you plan to do. walk to Austria?

780
00:55:08.263 --> 00:55:09.765
If that's what it takes.

781
00:55:09.848 --> 00:55:11.993
You heard the colonel.
Your friend is most likely dead.

782
00:55:12.017 --> 00:55:13.018
You don't know that.

783
00:55:13.101 --> 00:55:14.996
Even so. he's devising a strategy.
If he detects...

784
00:55:15.020 --> 00:55:18.023
By the time he's done that.
it could be too late.

785
00:55:18.106 --> 00:55:19.106
Steve!

786
00:55:25.531 --> 00:55:29.701
You told me you thought I was meant
for more than this. Did you mean that?

787
00:55:31.286 --> 00:55:32.704
Every word.

788
00:55:34.289 --> 00:55:35.332
Then you got to let me go.

789
00:55:39.086 --> 00:55:40.879
I can do more than that.

790
00:55:41.088 --> 00:55:44.091
Man: On stage. girls. Five minutes!

791
00:55:45.676 --> 00:55:47.052
Where's my helmet?

792
00:55:47.135 --> 00:55:48.428
Anyone seen Rogers?

793
00:55:52.307 --> 00:55:54.268
Peggy: The hydra camp
is in krausberg.

794
00:55:54.351 --> 00:55:56.436
tucked between
these two mountain ranges.

795
00:55:56.520 --> 00:55:57.646
It's a factory of some kind.

796
00:55:57.729 --> 00:56:00.065
We should be able to
drop you right on the doorstep.

797
00:56:00.148 --> 00:56:01.775
Just get me as close as you can.

798
00:56:01.900 --> 00:56:03.545
You two are gonna be
in a lot of trouble when you land.

799
00:56:03.569 --> 00:56:04.695
And you won't?

800
00:56:04.778 --> 00:56:07.131
Where I'm going. if anybody yells at me.
I can just shoot them.

801
00:56:07.155 --> 00:56:08.949
They will undoubtedly shoot back.

802
00:56:09.074 --> 00:56:11.076
Well. let's hope it's good for something.

803
00:56:11.159 --> 00:56:12.160
Howard: Agent Carter?

804
00:56:12.244 --> 00:56:13.555
If we're not in too much of a hurry.

805
00:56:13.579 --> 00:56:17.040
I thought we could stop off in lucerne
for a late-night fondue.

806
00:56:22.337 --> 00:56:25.132
Stark is the best civilian pilot
I've ever seen.

807
00:56:25.382 --> 00:56:28.010
He's mad enough to brave this airspace.
We're lucky to have him.

808
00:56:29.720 --> 00:56:31.471
So. are you two... do you...

809
00:56:33.974 --> 00:56:35.183
Fondue?

810
00:56:36.143 --> 00:56:38.395
This is your transponder.
Activate it when you're ready

811
00:56:38.520 --> 00:56:41.023
and the signal will lead us
straight to you.

812
00:56:42.149 --> 00:56:43.984
Are you sure this thing works?

813
00:56:44.109 --> 00:56:46.194
It's been tested more than you. pal.

814
00:56:46.361 --> 00:56:47.404
(Gunfire blasting)

815
00:56:51.366 --> 00:56:54.036
Get back here!
We're taking you all the way in!

816
00:56:55.787 --> 00:56:58.867
As soon as I'm clear. you turn this thing
around and get the hell out of here!

817
00:56:59.041 --> 00:57:01.043
You can't give me orders!

818
00:57:01.168 --> 00:57:04.004
The hell I can't! I'm a captain!

819
00:57:22.230 --> 00:57:26.568
As you can see. production of
the valkyrie is progressing on schedule.

820
00:57:26.652 --> 00:57:29.071
even with components of this size.

821
00:57:29.196 --> 00:57:32.074
Increase the output by 60%

822
00:57:32.199 --> 00:57:36.036
and see to it our other facilities
do the same.

823
00:57:36.411 --> 00:57:40.832
But these prisoners.
I'm not sure they have the strength.

824
00:57:41.249 --> 00:57:44.252
Then use up what strength
they have left. doctor.

825
00:57:44.628 --> 00:57:47.422
There are always more workers.

826
00:57:49.424 --> 00:57:50.634
Not now!

827
00:58:06.066 --> 00:58:07.859
You know. Fritz.

828
00:58:08.860 --> 00:58:11.279
one of these days.
I'm gonna have a stick of my own.

829
00:58:25.335 --> 00:58:27.254
(Shouting in distance)

830
00:58:44.354 --> 00:58:45.354
Fellas.

831
00:58:45.856 --> 00:58:46.940
Ah!

832
00:59:17.512 --> 00:59:19.389
(Indistinct chatter over pa)

833
00:59:44.581 --> 00:59:45.791
(Tapping at door)

834
01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:38.218
(Metallic clanking)

835
01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:44.432
(Keys rattling)

836
01:00:47.018 --> 01:00:48.436
Who are you supposed to be?

837
01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:51.982
I'm captain america.

838
01:00:53.275 --> 01:00:54.609
I beg your pardon?

839
01:00:58.071 --> 01:00:59.865
Dugan: What. are we taking everybody?

840
01:01:00.282 --> 01:01:01.825
I'm from Fresno. ace.

841
01:01:02.033 --> 01:01:04.744
Is there anybody else? I'm looking
for a sergeant James Barnes.

842
01:01:05.078 --> 01:01:08.158
There's an isolation ward in the factory.
but no one's ever come back from it.

843
01:01:08.206 --> 01:01:09.374
All right.

844
01:01:09.457 --> 01:01:11.457
The tree line is northwest.
80 yards past the gate.

845
01:01:11.501 --> 01:01:13.628
Get out fast and give 'em hell.

846
01:01:13.753 --> 01:01:15.439
I'll meet you guys in the clearing
with anybody else I find.

847
01:01:15.463 --> 01:01:18.216
Wait. You know what you're doing?

848
01:01:18.300 --> 01:01:21.094
Yeah. I've knocked out Adolf Hitler
over 200 times.

849
01:01:25.432 --> 01:01:26.850
(Shouting)

850
01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:47.430
Morita: You know
how to use that thing?

851
01:01:47.454 --> 01:01:48.496
(Gun powering up)

852
01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:52.834
Okay.

853
01:01:55.128 --> 01:01:56.504
What is happening?

854
01:01:58.548 --> 01:02:00.508
(Alarm sounding)

855
01:02:04.888 --> 01:02:06.890
Hey. Not exactly a buick.

856
01:02:08.475 --> 01:02:10.435
- That one. "Zcindung."
- Z£indung?

857
01:02:11.228 --> 01:02:12.330
Get this thing going. dugan!

858
01:02:12.354 --> 01:02:13.605
I didn't know you spoke German.

859
01:02:13.688 --> 01:02:16.900
Three semesters at Howard.
switched to French. girls much cuter.

860
01:02:17.025 --> 01:02:18.068
Didn't ask for the résumé.

861
01:02:22.489 --> 01:02:23.573
(Yelling)

862
01:02:27.327 --> 01:02:28.370
(Groaning)

863
01:02:28.495 --> 01:02:29.579
(Alarm continuing)

864
01:02:30.747 --> 01:02:32.249
- On your left!
- Up top!

865
01:02:49.724 --> 01:02:52.143
No. no! What are you doing?

866
01:02:53.186 --> 01:02:56.189
Our forces are outmatched.

867
01:02:56.481 --> 01:02:58.108
(Timer ticking)

868
01:03:10.870 --> 01:03:11.997
(Grunting)

869
01:03:20.755 --> 01:03:23.633
Keep moving! Grab those grenades!

870
01:03:56.291 --> 01:03:57.834
(Man groaning)

871
01:04:03.089 --> 01:04:06.176
Man: Sergeant.
Three-two-five-five-seven.

872
01:04:07.260 --> 01:04:08.303
Steve: Bucky?

873
01:04:09.387 --> 01:04:10.430
Oh. my god.

874
01:04:15.477 --> 01:04:16.853
- Is that...
- It's me.

875
01:04:17.103 --> 01:04:18.980
- It's Steve.
- Steve?

876
01:04:19.064 --> 01:04:20.648
- Come on.
- Steve.

877
01:04:24.569 --> 01:04:25.779
I thought you were dead.

878
01:04:26.654 --> 01:04:28.114
I thought you were smaller.

879
01:04:32.077 --> 01:04:33.453
(Guns firing distantly)

880
01:04:35.997 --> 01:04:37.082
Come on.

881
01:04:37.624 --> 01:04:38.833
(Grunting)

882
01:04:39.626 --> 01:04:42.420
- What happened to you?
- I joined the army.

883
01:04:48.593 --> 01:04:50.678
- Did it hurt?
- A little.

884
01:04:51.221 --> 01:04:52.555
Is this permanent?

885
01:04:52.639 --> 01:04:53.681
So far.

886
01:04:56.559 --> 01:04:58.228
(Shouting)

887
01:05:23.711 --> 01:05:25.505
Schmidt: Captain america!

888
01:05:25.588 --> 01:05:27.424
How exciting!

889
01:05:27.799 --> 01:05:30.802
I am a great fan of your films!

890
01:05:32.637 --> 01:05:36.641
So. Dr. Erskine managed it after all.

891
01:05:36.808 --> 01:05:38.601
Not exactly an improvement.

892
01:05:38.685 --> 01:05:42.105
but still. impressive.

893
01:05:44.816 --> 01:05:46.443
You've got no idea.

894
01:05:49.529 --> 01:05:50.655
Haven't I?

895
01:05:53.491 --> 01:05:54.534
(Grunting)

896
01:06:06.171 --> 01:06:09.257
No matter what lies erskine told you.

897
01:06:09.549 --> 01:06:12.802
you see. I was his greatest success!

898
01:06:26.149 --> 01:06:27.942
You don't have one of those. do you?

899
01:06:28.276 --> 01:06:30.695
You are deluded. captain.

900
01:06:31.279 --> 01:06:33.865
You pretend to be a simple soldier.

901
01:06:33.948 --> 01:06:36.493
but in reality. you are just afraid

902
01:06:36.576 --> 01:06:40.163
to admit that
we have left humanity behind.

903
01:06:41.873 --> 01:06:44.792
Unlike you. I embrace it proudly.

904
01:06:45.752 --> 01:06:46.878
Without fear!

905
01:06:47.170 --> 01:06:48.588
Then how come you're running?

906
01:06:52.425 --> 01:06:53.551
(Explosion)

907
01:07:00.642 --> 01:07:02.769
Come on. let's go. Up.

908
01:07:05.647 --> 01:07:07.899
Sir? Are we going to the roof?

909
01:07:11.528 --> 01:07:12.695
What about me?

910
01:07:12.946 --> 01:07:14.739
Where will I sit?

911
01:07:15.448 --> 01:07:17.158
Not a scratch. doctor.

912
01:07:17.325 --> 01:07:18.701
Not a scratch.

913
01:07:24.749 --> 01:07:25.833
(Explosion)

914
01:07:33.758 --> 01:07:35.009
(Grunting)

915
01:07:41.724 --> 01:07:42.976
(Car engine starting)

916
01:07:51.734 --> 01:07:53.987
Let's go. One at a time.

917
01:08:22.807 --> 01:08:25.810
- Gotta be a rope or something!
- Just go! Get out of here!

918
01:08:25.893 --> 01:08:27.103
No! Not without you!

919
01:08:28.021 --> 01:08:29.439
(Grunts)

920
01:08:30.440 --> 01:08:31.816
(Metal groaning)

921
01:08:50.627 --> 01:08:53.838
Phillips: Senator Brandt.
I regret to report that

922
01:08:53.921 --> 01:08:58.926
captain Steven g. Rogers went missing
behind enemy lines on the third.

923
01:08:59.010 --> 01:09:01.012
Aerial reconnaissance
has proven unfruitful.

924
01:09:01.095 --> 01:09:05.099
As a result.
I must declare captain Rogers

925
01:09:05.892 --> 01:09:08.102
killed in action. Period.

926
01:09:12.106 --> 01:09:13.816
The last surveillance flight is back.

927
01:09:16.319 --> 01:09:18.321
No sign of activity.

928
01:09:19.030 --> 01:09:21.783
- Go get a cup of coffee. corporal.
- Yes. sir.

929
01:09:24.535 --> 01:09:25.745
I can't touch stark.

930
01:09:25.870 --> 01:09:28.665
He's rich and he's the army's
number one weapons contractor.

931
01:09:28.748 --> 01:09:30.124
You are neither one.

932
01:09:30.249 --> 01:09:32.877
With respect. sir.
I don't regret my actions.

933
01:09:32.960 --> 01:09:34.647
And I don't think
captain Rogers did. either.

934
01:09:34.671 --> 01:09:37.465
What makes you think
I give a damn about your opinions?

935
01:09:37.548 --> 01:09:39.342
I took a chance with you. agent Carter.

936
01:09:39.467 --> 01:09:42.929
And now america's golden boy
and a lot of other good men are dead

937
01:09:43.054 --> 01:09:44.097
'cause you had a crush.

938
01:09:44.222 --> 01:09:46.683
It wasn't that. I had faith.

939
01:09:46.933 --> 01:09:51.688
Well. I hope that's a big comfort to you
when they shut this division down.

940
01:09:54.065 --> 01:09:55.483
What the hell's going on out there?

941
01:10:38.359 --> 01:10:40.111
Man: Look who it is!

942
01:10:40.737 --> 01:10:42.780
(All cheering)

943
01:11:07.305 --> 01:11:09.432
Some of these men
need medical attention.

944
01:11:09.557 --> 01:11:11.535
Man 2: Medic. we got wounded.
Medic: Right over here.

945
01:11:11.559 --> 01:11:14.103
I'd like to surrender myself
for disciplinary action.

946
01:11:15.563 --> 01:11:17.148
That won't be necessary.

947
01:11:20.943 --> 01:11:22.320
Yes. sir.

948
01:11:23.988 --> 01:11:25.364
Faflh. huh?

949
01:11:31.954 --> 01:11:33.372
You're late.

950
01:11:37.168 --> 01:11:39.003
Couldn't call my ride.

951
01:11:43.007 --> 01:11:44.467
Let's hear it for captain america!

952
01:11:44.592 --> 01:11:46.469
(All cheering)

953
01:12:01.609 --> 01:12:04.987
Brandt: I am honored
to present this medal for valor

954
01:12:05.071 --> 01:12:08.658
to my personal friend. captain america!

955
01:12:11.202 --> 01:12:13.037
Captain america!

956
01:12:14.455 --> 01:12:16.457
Captain. that's your cue!

957
01:12:20.211 --> 01:12:22.004
I thought he'd be taller.

958
01:12:34.225 --> 01:12:37.311
Steve: The fifth one was here
in Poland. right near the baltic.

959
01:12:37.436 --> 01:12:39.647
And the sixth one was

960
01:12:40.022 --> 01:12:45.027
about here. 30. 40 miles west
of the maginot line.

961
01:12:47.029 --> 01:12:48.865
I just got a quick look.

962
01:12:49.448 --> 01:12:51.450
Well. nobody's perfect.

963
01:12:54.829 --> 01:12:57.039
Steve: These are the weapon factories
we know about.

964
01:12:57.623 --> 01:12:59.417
Sergeant Barnes said
that hydra shipped

965
01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:02.169
all the parts to another facility
that isn't on this map.

966
01:13:02.253 --> 01:13:03.880
Agent Carter. coordinate with MI6.

967
01:13:03.963 --> 01:13:06.549
I want every allied eyeball
looking for that main hydra base.

968
01:13:06.674 --> 01:13:07.758
What about us?

969
01:13:07.884 --> 01:13:10.553
We are going to set a fire
under Johann schmidt's ass.

970
01:13:10.678 --> 01:13:12.680
What do you say. Rogers? It's your map.

971
01:13:12.763 --> 01:13:16.309
- You think you can wipe hydra off it?
- Yes. sir. I'll need a team.

972
01:13:16.851 --> 01:13:18.895
We're already putting together
the best men.

973
01:13:19.061 --> 01:13:22.106
With all due respect. sir. so am I.

974
01:13:23.274 --> 01:13:24.775
So. let's get this straight.

975
01:13:24.901 --> 01:13:27.301
We barely got out of there alive.
and you want us to go back?

976
01:13:28.529 --> 01:13:29.864
Pretty much.

977
01:13:29.947 --> 01:13:32.116
Sounds rather fun. actually.

978
01:13:32.700 --> 01:13:33.784
(Belching)

979
01:13:33.951 --> 01:13:34.994
I'm in.

980
01:13:35.119 --> 01:13:39.123
(Dernier speaking French)

981
01:13:40.082 --> 01:13:41.709
(Speaking French)

982
01:13:41.792 --> 01:13:43.169
(Laughing)

983
01:13:44.378 --> 01:13:45.922
(Chuckung)

984
01:13:47.506 --> 01:13:48.925
We're in.

985
01:13:49.926 --> 01:13:53.137
Hell. I'll always fight.
But you got to do one thing for me.

986
01:13:53.220 --> 01:13:54.220
What's that?

987
01:13:56.265 --> 01:13:57.308
Open a tab.

988
01:13:58.142 --> 01:13:59.435
(All laughing)

989
01:14:01.103 --> 01:14:02.730
Morita: Well. that was easy.

990
01:14:03.147 --> 01:14:05.524
- Another round.
- Where are they putting all this stuff?

991
01:14:08.277 --> 01:14:09.320
(Men singing)

992
01:14:09.528 --> 01:14:11.739
See? I told you.

993
01:14:12.281 --> 01:14:14.283
They're all idiots.

994
01:14:14.951 --> 01:14:16.118
How about you?

995
01:14:17.119 --> 01:14:20.164
You ready to follow captain america
into the jaws of death?

996
01:14:20.289 --> 01:14:21.457
Hell. no.

997
01:14:21.540 --> 01:14:26.170
That little guy from Brooklyn who was
too dumb not to run away from a fight.

998
01:14:27.129 --> 01:14:28.965
I'm following him.

999
01:14:32.343 --> 01:14:33.886
But you're keeping the outfit. right?

1000
01:14:36.597 --> 01:14:37.682
You know what?

1001
01:14:39.100 --> 01:14:40.559
It's kind of growing on me.

1002
01:14:40.685 --> 01:14:43.020
(All singing)

1003
01:14:51.696 --> 01:14:53.197
- Peggy: Captain.
- Agent Carter.

1004
01:14:55.783 --> 01:14:56.826
Ma'am.

1005
01:14:56.951 --> 01:14:59.912
Howard has some equipment for you
to try. Tomorrow morning?

1006
01:14:59.996 --> 01:15:01.163
Sounds good.

1007
01:15:06.002 --> 01:15:08.713
I see your top squad
is prepping for duty.

1008
01:15:09.171 --> 01:15:10.214
You don't like music?

1009
01:15:10.339 --> 01:15:11.590
I do. actually.

1010
01:15:13.300 --> 01:15:16.929
I might even.
when this is all over. go dancing.

1011
01:15:17.346 --> 01:15:18.514
Then what are we waiting for?

1012
01:15:19.390 --> 01:15:21.142
The right partner.

1013
01:15:22.226 --> 01:15:23.394
0800. captain.

1014
01:15:24.603 --> 01:15:27.023
Yes. ma'am. I'll be there.

1015
01:15:27.189 --> 01:15:28.941
I'm invisible.

1016
01:15:29.316 --> 01:15:32.403
I'm turning into you.
It's like a horrible dream.

1017
01:15:33.154 --> 01:15:36.240
Don't take it so hard.
Maybe she's got a friend.

1018
01:15:37.825 --> 01:15:40.411
Howard:
Emission signature is unusual.

1019
01:15:41.037 --> 01:15:43.039
Alpha and beta ray neutral.

1020
01:15:44.331 --> 01:15:46.834
Though I doubt
Rogers picked up on that.

1021
01:15:48.419 --> 01:15:49.837
Seems harmless enough.

1022
01:15:51.255 --> 01:15:53.174
Hard to see what all the fuss is about.

1023
01:16:02.558 --> 01:16:03.976
Write that down.

1024
01:16:05.853 --> 01:16:08.564
Excuse me. I'm looking for a Mr. Stark.

1025
01:16:08.647 --> 01:16:10.775
He's in with colonel Phillips.

1026
01:16:15.446 --> 01:16:18.240
Of course. you're welcome to wait.

1027
01:16:24.914 --> 01:16:27.083
I read about what you did.

1028
01:16:27.374 --> 01:16:29.210
Oh. the... yeah.

1029
01:16:29.877 --> 01:16:31.378
Well. that's. you know.

1030
01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:34.449
Just doing what needed to be done.

1031
01:16:34.799 --> 01:16:37.635
Sounded like more than that.
You saved nearly 400 men.

1032
01:16:44.016 --> 01:16:46.018
Really. it's not a big deal.

1033
01:16:46.852 --> 01:16:49.063
Tell that to their wives.

1034
01:16:52.358 --> 01:16:54.026
I don't think they were all married.

1035
01:16:54.235 --> 01:16:55.694
You're a hero.

1036
01:16:55.820 --> 01:16:58.447
Well. that depends
on the definition. really.

1037
01:16:58.531 --> 01:17:01.700
The women of america.
they owe you their thanks.

1038
01:17:02.910 --> 01:17:05.913
And seeing as they're not here...

1039
01:17:14.421 --> 01:17:15.464
Captain!

1040
01:17:15.548 --> 01:17:18.384
We're ready for you.
if you're not othennise occupied.

1041
01:17:19.301 --> 01:17:21.011
Agent Carter. wait.

1042
01:17:21.095 --> 01:17:23.472
Looks like finding a partner
wasn't that hard after all.

1043
01:17:23.556 --> 01:17:25.117
Peggy. that's not
what you thought it was.

1044
01:17:25.141 --> 01:17:27.726
I don't think anything. captain.
not one thing.

1045
01:17:28.060 --> 01:17:31.647
You always wanted to be a soldier.
and now you are. just like all the rest.

1046
01:17:31.939 --> 01:17:33.125
Well. what about you and stark?

1047
01:17:33.149 --> 01:17:35.526
How do I know you two
haven't been fondue-ing?

1048
01:17:40.447 --> 01:17:42.867
You still don't know
a bloody thing about women.

1049
01:17:44.326 --> 01:17:46.328
Howard: Fondue is just
cheese and bread. my friend.

1050
01:17:46.453 --> 01:17:49.498
- Really? I didn't think...
- Nor should you. pal.

1051
01:17:49.582 --> 01:17:51.434
The moment you think you know
what's going on in a woman's head

1052
01:17:51.458 --> 01:17:53.919
is the moment your goose
is well and truly cooked.

1053
01:17:54.003 --> 01:17:56.672
Me. I concentrate on work.
which at the moment

1054
01:17:56.755 --> 01:17:59.550
is about making sure you and your men
do not get killed.

1055
01:17:59.884 --> 01:18:01.552
Carbon polymer.

1056
01:18:02.344 --> 01:18:04.555
Should withstand
your average German bayonet.

1057
01:18:04.680 --> 01:18:08.309
Although hydra's not going to
attack you with a pocket knife.

1058
01:18:08.475 --> 01:18:11.395
I hear you're kind of attached.

1059
01:18:11.520 --> 01:18:12.873
It's handier than you might think.

1060
01:18:12.897 --> 01:18:15.107
I took the Liberty
of coming up with some options.

1061
01:18:15.691 --> 01:18:16.775
This one's fun.

1062
01:18:17.526 --> 01:18:20.196
She's been fitted with electrical relays
that allow you to...

1063
01:18:20.321 --> 01:18:21.882
- What about this one?
- No. no. that's just a prototype.

1064
01:18:21.906 --> 01:18:24.116
- What's it made of?
- Vibranium.

1065
01:18:25.201 --> 01:18:27.786
It's stronger than steel
and a third the weight.

1066
01:18:28.537 --> 01:18:31.332
It's completely vibration absorbent.

1067
01:18:33.292 --> 01:18:34.752
How come it's not standard issue?

1068
01:18:34.877 --> 01:18:36.337
That's the rarest metal on earth.

1069
01:18:36.420 --> 01:18:38.106
What you're holding there.
that's all we've got.

1070
01:18:38.130 --> 01:18:40.382
You quite finished. Mr. Stark?

1071
01:18:40.507 --> 01:18:42.402
I'm sure the captain
has some unfinished business.

1072
01:18:42.426 --> 01:18:44.345
What do you think?

1073
01:18:49.433 --> 01:18:51.101
(Metal reverberating)

1074
01:18:54.146 --> 01:18:56.148
Yes. I think it works.

1075
01:19:05.449 --> 01:19:07.409
I had some ideas about the uniform.

1076
01:19:07.743 --> 01:19:09.411
Whatever you want. pal.

1077
01:19:56.417 --> 01:19:57.459
(Grunting)

1078
01:20:08.012 --> 01:20:09.388
(Whistling)

1079
01:20:23.819 --> 01:20:24.903
(Laughing)

1080
01:20:25.029 --> 01:20:26.488
(Projector whirring)

1081
01:20:50.596 --> 01:20:52.306
(Gunfire)

1082
01:21:01.440 --> 01:21:02.524
(Screaming)

1083
01:21:13.952 --> 01:21:16.372
You are failing!

1084
01:21:17.247 --> 01:21:20.584
We are close to an offensive
that will shake the planet.

1085
01:21:20.709 --> 01:21:22.669
yet we are continually delayed

1086
01:21:22.753 --> 01:21:25.339
because you cannot outwit
a simpleton with a shield!

1087
01:21:25.464 --> 01:21:27.466
This is hardly my area of expertise.

1088
01:21:27.549 --> 01:21:31.178
I merely developed the weapons.
I cannot fire them.

1089
01:21:32.554 --> 01:21:35.682
Finish your mission. doctor.
before the American finishes his.

1090
01:21:36.558 --> 01:21:37.601
Man: Sir!

1091
01:21:39.728 --> 01:21:40.771
I'm sorry. herr schmidt.

1092
01:21:42.481 --> 01:21:44.274
We fought to the last man.

1093
01:21:47.611 --> 01:21:49.488
Evidently not.

1094
01:21:49.571 --> 01:21:50.697
(Laser firing)

1095
01:21:53.575 --> 01:21:55.702
(Indistinct chatter over radio)

1096
01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:04.878
Remember when I made you ride
the cyclone at coney island?

1097
01:22:04.962 --> 01:22:06.547
Yeah. and I threw up?

1098
01:22:07.923 --> 01:22:09.550
This isn't payback. is it?

1099
01:22:09.633 --> 01:22:11.343
Now why would I do that?

1100
01:22:11.427 --> 01:22:14.138
Jones: We were right.
Dr. Zola's on the train.

1101
01:22:14.221 --> 01:22:17.683
Hydra dispatcher gave him permission
to open up the throttle.

1102
01:22:17.766 --> 01:22:19.685
Wherever he's going.
they must need him bad.

1103
01:22:26.775 --> 01:22:29.236
Let's get going.
because they're moving like the devil.

1104
01:22:29.778 --> 01:22:31.655
We only got about a 10-second window.

1105
01:22:31.780 --> 01:22:34.241
You miss that window.
we're bugs on a windshield.

1106
01:22:34.700 --> 01:22:35.742
Mind the gap.

1107
01:22:35.826 --> 01:22:37.744
Better get moving. bugs!

1108
01:22:39.329 --> 01:22:40.747
(Dernier yelling in French)

1109
01:23:42.017 --> 01:23:43.268
(Gun charging)

1110
01:23:45.771 --> 01:23:47.648
Stop him! Fire again!

1111
01:24:01.870 --> 01:24:03.288
(Gun charging)

1112
01:24:29.064 --> 01:24:30.107
(Gun firing)

1113
01:24:35.821 --> 01:24:36.822
(Grunting)

1114
01:24:40.409 --> 01:24:42.869
- I had him on the ropes.
- I know you did.

1115
01:24:43.662 --> 01:24:44.746
Get down!

1116
01:24:46.790 --> 01:24:48.208
Fire again!

1117
01:24:48.875 --> 01:24:50.627
Kill him! Now!

1118
01:24:57.884 --> 01:24:58.884
Bucky!

1119
01:25:02.723 --> 01:25:04.308
Hang on!

1120
01:25:05.851 --> 01:25:06.893
Grab my hand!

1121
01:25:09.104 --> 01:25:10.397
(Screaming)

1122
01:25:28.707 --> 01:25:29.958
(Gun cocking)

1123
01:26:04.701 --> 01:26:05.744
(Door opening)

1124
01:26:09.831 --> 01:26:10.957
(Door shutting loudly)

1125
01:26:12.626 --> 01:26:13.794
Sit down.

1126
01:26:20.342 --> 01:26:22.761
- What is this?
- Steak.

1127
01:26:23.637 --> 01:26:24.846
What is in it?

1128
01:26:25.972 --> 01:26:27.140
Cow.

1129
01:26:30.227 --> 01:26:33.230
Doctor. do you realize how difficult it is

1130
01:26:33.355 --> 01:26:36.149
to get a hold of a prime out like that
out here?

1131
01:26:37.651 --> 01:26:38.944
I don't eat meat.

1132
01:26:39.820 --> 01:26:40.987
Why not?

1133
01:26:41.113 --> 01:26:42.823
It disagrees with me.

1134
01:26:42.906 --> 01:26:45.992
How about cyanide? Does that give you
the rumbly tummy. too?

1135
01:26:48.870 --> 01:26:51.832
Every hydra agent that
we've tried to take alive

1136
01:26:51.957 --> 01:26:57.003
has crunched a little pill before
we can stop him. But not you.

1137
01:26:58.004 --> 01:27:00.799
So. here is my brilliant theory.

1138
01:27:02.843 --> 01:27:04.261
You want to live.

1139
01:27:05.679 --> 01:27:07.889
You're trying to intimidate me. colonel.

1140
01:27:08.390 --> 01:27:09.933
I bought you dinner.

1141
01:27:15.188 --> 01:27:18.358
"Given the valuable information
he has provided

1142
01:27:18.984 --> 01:27:22.779
"and in exchange for
his full cooperation.

1143
01:27:22.988 --> 01:27:25.991
"Dr. Zola is being remanded
to Switzerland"?

1144
01:27:26.074 --> 01:27:29.953
I sent that message to Washington
this morning. of course it was encoded.

1145
01:27:30.787 --> 01:27:34.291
You guys haven't broken those codes.
have you? That would be awkward.

1146
01:27:34.416 --> 01:27:36.418
Schmidt will know this is a lie.

1147
01:27:36.501 --> 01:27:40.005
He's going to kill you anyway. doc.
You're a liability.

1148
01:27:40.505 --> 01:27:42.507
You know more about schmidt
than anyone.

1149
01:27:42.924 --> 01:27:47.929
And the last guy you cost us
was captain Rogers' closest friend.

1150
01:27:48.013 --> 01:27:50.974
so I wouldn't count on
the very best of protection.

1151
01:27:51.850 --> 01:27:54.436
It's you or schmidt.

1152
01:27:54.895 --> 01:27:57.022
It's just the hand you've been dealt.

1153
01:27:59.733 --> 01:28:02.903
Schmidt believes he walks
in the footsteps of the gods.

1154
01:28:03.278 --> 01:28:04.404
Hmm.

1155
01:28:04.529 --> 01:28:07.282
Only the world itself will satisfy him.

1156
01:28:07.407 --> 01:28:09.701
You do realize that's nuts. don't you?

1157
01:28:09.826 --> 01:28:10.869
What?

1158
01:28:11.828 --> 01:28:13.997
The sanity of the plan
is of no consequence.

1159
01:28:14.080 --> 01:28:16.124
- And why is that?
- Because he can do it!

1160
01:28:16.958 --> 01:28:18.126
What's his target?

1161
01:28:19.461 --> 01:28:21.922
Hbema

1162
01:28:23.340 --> 01:28:24.466
is everywhere.

1163
01:28:45.237 --> 01:28:47.072
Tomorrow.

1164
01:28:47.697 --> 01:28:51.117
hydra will stand master of the world.

1165
01:28:51.785 --> 01:28:54.162
borne to victory on the wings
of the valkyrie.

1166
01:28:55.330 --> 01:28:59.251
Our enemies' weapons
will be powerless against us.

1167
01:29:00.001 --> 01:29:05.006
If they shoot down one plane.
hundreds more will rain fire upon them!

1168
01:29:09.344 --> 01:29:11.888
If they cut off one head.

1169
01:29:12.264 --> 01:29:14.975
two more shall take its place.

1170
01:29:15.392 --> 01:29:16.810
Hail hydra.

1171
01:29:17.143 --> 01:29:18.186
- Hail hydra!
- Hail hydra!

1172
01:29:18.728 --> 01:29:21.314
- Hail hydra! Hail hydra!
- Hail hydra! Hail hydra!

1173
01:29:23.108 --> 01:29:25.360
(All shouting)

1174
01:29:33.285 --> 01:29:36.079
Man on radio: Blackout is still
in effect throughout the London area.

1175
01:29:36.496 --> 01:29:38.498
Please wait for the all-clear.

1176
01:29:38.915 --> 01:29:43.920
Your attention. please. All citizens shall
remain indoors until further notice.

1177
01:29:44.504 --> 01:29:47.591
Blackout is still in effect
throughout the London area.

1178
01:29:55.557 --> 01:29:57.559
Dr. Erskine said that

1179
01:29:57.976 --> 01:30:00.353
the serum wouldn't
just affect my muscles.

1180
01:30:00.437 --> 01:30:02.564
it would affect my cells.

1181
01:30:03.565 --> 01:30:07.360
Create a protective system
of regeneration and healing.

1182
01:30:07.444 --> 01:30:09.029
Which means

1183
01:30:11.364 --> 01:30:13.199
I can't get drunk.

1184
01:30:14.951 --> 01:30:16.119
Did you know that?

1185
01:30:16.578 --> 01:30:20.957
Your metabolism burns four times faster
than the average person.

1186
01:30:22.542 --> 01:30:25.128
He thought it could be
one of the side effects.

1187
01:30:30.133 --> 01:30:32.135
It wasn't your fault.

1188
01:30:33.261 --> 01:30:35.096
- Did you read the report?
- Yes.

1189
01:30:36.056 --> 01:30:37.432
Then you know that's not true.

1190
01:30:37.557 --> 01:30:39.267
You did everything you could.

1191
01:30:42.771 --> 01:30:44.898
Did you believe in your friend?

1192
01:30:45.023 --> 01:30:46.399
Did you respect him?

1193
01:30:48.193 --> 01:30:50.070
Then stop blaming yourself.

1194
01:30:50.236 --> 01:30:52.697
Allow Barnes the dignity of his choice.

1195
01:30:53.198 --> 01:30:55.118
He damn well must have thought
you were worth it.

1196
01:30:57.285 --> 01:30:58.787
I'm going after schmidt.

1197
01:31:00.246 --> 01:31:03.667
I'm not gonna stop until all of hydra
is dead or captured.

1198
01:31:05.585 --> 01:31:07.170
You won't be alone.

1199
01:31:09.547 --> 01:31:13.134
Johann schmidt belongs in a bughouse.
He thinks he's a god.

1200
01:31:13.218 --> 01:31:15.237
and he's willing to blow up
half the world to prove it.

1201
01:31:15.261 --> 01:31:16.721
starting with the usa.

1202
01:31:16.846 --> 01:31:20.016
Schmidt's working with powers
beyond our capabilities.

1203
01:31:20.100 --> 01:31:21.810
He gets across the Atlantic.

1204
01:31:21.893 --> 01:31:24.187
he will wipe out
the entire eastern seaboard in an hour.

1205
01:31:28.733 --> 01:31:30.276
How much time we got?

1206
01:31:30.402 --> 01:31:32.696
According to my new best friend.
under 24 hours.

1207
01:31:32.821 --> 01:31:35.824
- Man: Where is he now?
- Hydra's last base is here.

1208
01:31:36.616 --> 01:31:40.161
In the alps. 500 feet below the surface.

1209
01:31:42.163 --> 01:31:43.516
Morita: So what are we
supposed to do?

1210
01:31:43.540 --> 01:31:46.292
I mean. it's not like
we can just knock on the front door.

1211
01:31:46.835 --> 01:31:48.253
Steve: Why not?

1212
01:31:53.341 --> 01:31:55.343
That's exactly what we're going to do.

1213
01:32:25.290 --> 01:32:26.666
(Screaming)

1214
01:32:35.175 --> 01:32:36.342
(Screaming)

1215
01:34:01.052 --> 01:34:05.223
Schmidt: Arrogance may not be
a uniquely American trait.

1216
01:34:05.348 --> 01:34:07.475
but I must say.
you do it better than anyone.

1217
01:34:10.395 --> 01:34:12.981
But there are limits

1218
01:34:13.398 --> 01:34:15.525
to what even you can do. captain.

1219
01:34:16.067 --> 01:34:19.404
Or did erskine tell you othennise?

1220
01:34:19.487 --> 01:34:20.822
He told me you were insane.

1221
01:34:25.451 --> 01:34:27.453
He resented my genius

1222
01:34:27.579 --> 01:34:31.291
and tried to deny me
what was rightfully mine.

1223
01:34:31.416 --> 01:34:32.876
But he gave you everything.

1224
01:34:38.423 --> 01:34:40.967
What made you so special?

1225
01:34:41.384 --> 01:34:42.468
(Chuckles)

1226
01:34:44.179 --> 01:34:45.388
Nothing.

1227
01:34:46.347 --> 01:34:48.016
I'm just a kid from Brooklyn.

1228
01:34:51.436 --> 01:34:52.979
(Coughing)

1229
01:34:59.402 --> 01:35:01.112
I can do this all day.

1230
01:35:01.237 --> 01:35:03.281
Of course you can. of course.

1231
01:35:03.406 --> 01:35:06.576
But. unfortunately.
I am on a tight schedule.

1232
01:35:12.415 --> 01:35:13.625
So am I.

1233
01:35:26.221 --> 01:35:28.806
Rogers! You might need this!

1234
01:35:29.265 --> 01:35:30.308
Thanks!

1235
01:35:41.569 --> 01:35:44.030
We're in! Assault team. go!

1236
01:35:44.280 --> 01:35:45.448
Move out!

1237
01:35:46.532 --> 01:35:48.284
Soldier: Move!

1238
01:35:54.082 --> 01:35:56.167
Phillips: Keep your spacing!

1239
01:36:04.550 --> 01:36:05.677
(Gasps)

1240
01:36:24.362 --> 01:36:25.530
- (Explosion)
- (Screaming)

1241
01:36:35.665 --> 01:36:37.917
Hydra soldier:
Cutoff one head. two more...

1242
01:36:39.544 --> 01:36:41.129
Let's go find two more!

1243
01:37:07.739 --> 01:37:08.781
You're late.

1244
01:37:11.743 --> 01:37:13.745
- Weren't you about to...
- Right.

1245
01:37:38.728 --> 01:37:39.937
(Mechanical whirring)

1246
01:38:28.528 --> 01:38:29.612
Get in!

1247
01:38:58.141 --> 01:38:59.559
- Keep it steady!
- Wait!

1248
01:39:05.022 --> 01:39:06.274
Go get him.

1249
01:39:08.234 --> 01:39:09.861
I'm not kissing you!

1250
01:39:27.879 --> 01:39:28.921
(Grunting)

1251
01:39:52.361 --> 01:39:54.113
(Mechanical whirring)

1252
01:40:18.179 --> 01:40:19.639
(Footsteps approaching)

1253
01:40:24.727 --> 01:40:25.811
(Grunting)

1254
01:40:46.624 --> 01:40:47.750
(Screaming)

1255
01:40:53.673 --> 01:40:54.840
(Screaming)

1256
01:41:33.963 --> 01:41:35.089
(Steve grunting)

1257
01:42:46.661 --> 01:42:47.745
(Laser charging)

1258
01:42:49.330 --> 01:42:52.541
- You don't give up. do you?
- Nope!

1259
01:43:09.266 --> 01:43:10.726
(Grunting)

1260
01:43:11.852 --> 01:43:13.396
(Schmidt choking)

1261
01:44:01.360 --> 01:44:04.071
You could have the power of the gods!

1262
01:44:04.655 --> 01:44:09.243
Yet you wear a flag on your chest
and think you fight a battle of nations!

1263
01:44:10.119 --> 01:44:12.329
I have seen the future. captain!

1264
01:44:13.205 --> 01:44:16.333
- There are no flags!
- Not my future!

1265
01:44:20.004 --> 01:44:21.130
(Grunting)

1266
01:44:30.139 --> 01:44:31.182
What have you done?

1267
01:45:02.087 --> 01:45:04.048
(Screaming)

1268
01:45:41.460 --> 01:45:43.855
Steve: (On radio) Come in. This is
captain Rogers. Do you read me?

1269
01:45:43.879 --> 01:45:45.119
Captain Rogers. what is your...

1270
01:45:45.172 --> 01:45:46.525
Steve. is that you? Are you all right?

1271
01:45:46.549 --> 01:45:48.008
Peggy. schmidt's dead!

1272
01:45:48.843 --> 01:45:50.261
Peggy: What about the plane?

1273
01:45:52.054 --> 01:45:53.681
That's a little bit tougher to explain.

1274
01:45:54.014 --> 01:45:56.475
Give me your coordinates.
I'll find you a safe landing site.

1275
01:45:57.852 --> 01:45:59.979
There's not gonna be a safe landing.

1276
01:46:00.062 --> 01:46:01.772
But I can try and force it down.

1277
01:46:01.897 --> 01:46:03.899
I'll get Howard on the line.
He'll know what to do.

1278
01:46:03.983 --> 01:46:05.067
There's not enough time.

1279
01:46:05.150 --> 01:46:07.736
This thing's moving too fast
and it's heading for New York.

1280
01:46:12.116 --> 01:46:14.118
I got to put her in the water.

1281
01:46:14.451 --> 01:46:17.079
Please. don't do this.
We have time. We can work it out.

1282
01:46:17.454 --> 01:46:18.682
Right now I'm in the middle of nowhere.

1283
01:46:18.706 --> 01:46:21.041
If I wait any longer.
a lot of people are gonna die.

1284
01:46:26.672 --> 01:46:27.923
Peggy.

1285
01:46:29.675 --> 01:46:31.051
this is my choice.

1286
01:46:55.075 --> 01:46:56.285
Peggy?

1287
01:46:57.077 --> 01:46:58.495
Peggy: I'm here.

1288
01:47:01.290 --> 01:47:04.084
I'm gonna need a rain check
on that dance.

1289
01:47:12.301 --> 01:47:13.510
All right.

1290
01:47:16.513 --> 01:47:18.974
A week. next Saturday.
at the stork club.

1291
01:47:20.309 --> 01:47:21.727
You got it.

1292
01:47:23.562 --> 01:47:27.566
8:00 on the dot.
Don't you dare be late. Understood?

1293
01:47:29.985 --> 01:47:32.154
You know.
I still don't know how to dance.

1294
01:47:38.118 --> 01:47:41.121
I'll show you how. Just be there.

1295
01:47:42.539 --> 01:47:44.124
We'll have the band
play something slow.

1296
01:47:48.170 --> 01:47:49.797
I'd hate to step on your...

1297
01:47:49.922 --> 01:47:51.090
(Radio static)

1298
01:47:52.967 --> 01:47:54.009
Steve?

1299
01:47:56.345 --> 01:47:57.763
Steve?

1300
01:48:01.183 --> 01:48:02.184
Steve? (Sobbing)

1301
01:48:16.615 --> 01:48:18.325
(Wind howling)

1302
01:48:48.772 --> 01:48:50.566
(Crowd cheering)

1303
01:49:01.243 --> 01:49:02.870
To the captain.

1304
01:49:15.049 --> 01:49:16.091
Man: Sir?

1305
01:49:26.143 --> 01:49:28.145
Take us to the next grid point.

1306
01:49:28.228 --> 01:49:30.314
But there's no trace of wreckage.

1307
01:49:31.148 --> 01:49:33.734
And the energy signature stops here.

1308
01:49:34.860 --> 01:49:36.528
Just keep looking.

1309
01:50:38.465 --> 01:50:40.259
(Indistinct chatter on radio)

1310
01:50:45.139 --> 01:50:47.724
Man on radio: Curve ball.
high and outside for ball one.

1311
01:50:49.017 --> 01:50:51.728
So the Dodgers are tied. 4-4.

1312
01:50:52.563 --> 01:50:55.023
And the crowd well knows that
with one swing of his bat.

1313
01:50:55.149 --> 01:50:57.985
this fellow's capable of making it
a brand-new game again.

1314
01:50:59.319 --> 01:51:02.531
Just an absolutely gorgeous day
here at ebbets field.

1315
01:51:03.323 --> 01:51:06.577
The Phillies have managed
to tie it up at 4-4.

1316
01:51:07.327 --> 01:51:09.746
But the Dodgers have three men on.

1317
01:51:14.376 --> 01:51:17.171
Pearson beaned Reiser
in Philadelphia last month.

1318
01:51:17.254 --> 01:51:20.465
Wouldn't the youngster like a hit here
to return the favor?

1319
01:51:20.757 --> 01:51:22.968
Pete leans in. Here's the pitch.

1320
01:51:23.385 --> 01:51:26.471
Swung on. A line to the right.
And it gets past Rizzo.

1321
01:51:28.390 --> 01:51:29.558
Three runs will score.

1322
01:51:29.975 --> 01:51:33.353
Reiser heads to third.
Durocher's going to wave him in.

1323
01:51:34.354 --> 01:51:35.957
Here comes the relay.
but they won't get him.

1324
01:51:35.981 --> 01:51:37.024
(Door opening)

1325
01:51:38.275 --> 01:51:39.359
Good morning.

1326
01:51:41.278 --> 01:51:42.988
Or should I say afternoon?

1327
01:51:44.072 --> 01:51:45.199
Where am I?

1328
01:51:45.866 --> 01:51:47.951
You're in a recovery room
in New York City.

1329
01:51:49.786 --> 01:51:53.415
Man on radio: The Dodgers take
the lead. 8-4. Oh. Dodgers!

1330
01:51:53.582 --> 01:51:55.375
Everyone is on their feet.

1331
01:51:55.792 --> 01:51:59.213
What a game we have here today. folks.
What a game. indeed.

1332
01:51:59.296 --> 01:52:00.422
Where am I really?

1333
01:52:01.798 --> 01:52:03.800
I'm afraid I don't understand.

1334
01:52:04.468 --> 01:52:05.886
The game.

1335
01:52:06.094 --> 01:52:09.014
It's from may 1941.
I know. 'cause I was there.

1336
01:52:13.018 --> 01:52:15.020
Now. I'm going to ask you again.

1337
01:52:15.437 --> 01:52:16.480
Where am I?

1338
01:52:17.856 --> 01:52:19.274
- Captain Rogers...
- Who are you?

1339
01:52:26.782 --> 01:52:28.367
Woman: Captain Rogers. wait!

1340
01:52:30.327 --> 01:52:32.037
All agents. code 13!

1341
01:52:32.371 --> 01:52:35.457
I repeat. All agents. code 13!

1342
01:52:40.712 --> 01:52:42.130
(Car horn honking)

1343
01:52:55.936 --> 01:52:57.437
Man: At ease. soldier!

1344
01:53:06.113 --> 01:53:09.032
Look. I'm sorry about that little show
back there.

1345
01:53:10.367 --> 01:53:13.370
but we thought it best
to break it to you slowly.

1346
01:53:13.578 --> 01:53:14.746
Break what?

1347
01:53:17.291 --> 01:53:18.875
You've been asleep. cap.

1348
01:53:19.459 --> 01:53:21.545
For almost 70 years.

1349
01:53:35.976 --> 01:53:37.311
You gonna be okay?

1350
01:53:38.395 --> 01:53:39.521
Yeah.

1351
01:53:39.688 --> 01:53:41.106
Yeah. I just...

1352
01:53:44.568 --> 01:53:45.736
I had a date.

1353
02:02:53.575 --> 02:02:55.660
(Breathing hard)

1354
02:03:07.672 --> 02:03:09.257
Nick: Trouble sleeping?

1355
02:03:12.051 --> 02:03:13.469
You're here with a mission. sir?

1356
02:03:14.387 --> 02:03:15.430
I am.

1357
02:03:16.055 --> 02:03:18.099
Trying to get me back in the world?

1358
02:03:19.100 --> 02:03:20.435
Trying to save it.

1359
02:03:29.485 --> 02:03:31.445
Nick: You think you're the only hero
in the world?

1360
02:03:45.501 --> 02:03:46.711
Nick: Gentlemen?

1361
02:03:47.420 --> 02:03:48.546
You're up.

1362
02:03:54.427 --> 02:03:55.470
Got a mean swing.
